title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Rub fondue pot or chafing dish with a clove of garlic.
Add all ingredients and warm slowly.
Serve with toasted bread cubes.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Chop onion in small pieces. Saute onion in frypan; add cooked rice, then add soy sauce to taste.
Stir until well blended and hot.
Serve with baked chicken or any other meat or fish dinner.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix soup, Cheez Whiz and butter; cook over low heat.
Combine the rest in bowl, then add cheese mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a well buttered baking dish.
Serves 8.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Cream together shortening, brown sugar and sugar until light and fluffy at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, mixing well with spoon.
Stir in oats, coconut and nuts.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place balls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: italian crescent bake
directions: Heat oven to 275 degrees. Brown hamburger and onion. Drain, stir in cooked spaghetti and tomato sauce. Heat and simmer just until all are well blended well. In another bowl, combine Mozzarella cheese and sour cream. Pour meat mixture into an ungreased baking dish. Spoon cheese mixture over meat. Place crescent rolls on top, making a crust covering. Combine melted butter and Parmesan cheese and spread on top. Bake until golden brown.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature.
Mix together cheese and other ingredients.
Form into 2 cheese balls.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain and arrange stalks in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top and sprinkle with almonds.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: party mints
directions: Mix and knead (will be stiff).
Form small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Press down with a fork.
Let sit to dry.

title: chinese cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers. Cut lengthwise and remove seeds with a spoon, then cut into 1/4-inch cross sections.

title: pineapple-cherry disaster
directions: Drain pineapple and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. cover pineapple with cherry filling.
Work lumps out of cake mix. Spread evenly over fruit.
Pour butter over cake mix and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°
until top is golden brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Stir together in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Add 1/2 teaspoon each of grated lemon and orange rind.
Cool and spoon over fruit.
Let stand until it sets.
Enjoy.

title: ham and egg salad
directions: Combine ham, rice, celery, onions and eggs.
Blend remaining ingredients and stir into ham mixture.
Mix well and chill.
Serve on salad greens.
Garnish with tomato wedges, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla cupcakes
directions: Cream together eggs, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Add to wet ingredients.

title: layer dessert
directions: Prepare pudding per instructions on box.
Set aside.
Break angel food cake into large pieces.
Cover bottom of deep glass dish with half of cake.
Cover cake with half of pudding.
Cover pudding with half of whipped topping.
Arrange 1/2 kiwi and 1/2 strawberries on whipped topping.
Repeat layers.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter and bring to a boil.
Beat eggs and add nuts.
Gradually add hot syrup mixture to egg-nut mixture.
Cool filling slightly.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate yeast cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add melted chocolate and yeast dissolved in warm water.
Add flour and milk slowly.
(You can put in icebox and finish next day.)
To finish, add vanilla and soda in 3 tablespoons hot water.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch loaf pan, approximately 35 minutes, at 350°.

title: cheesy potato chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare mashed potatoes; stir in 1/2 cup of cheese.
Spread in ungreased pan.
Mix chicken, broccoli, gravy and pepper.
Spread over potato mixture.
Mix remaining cheese and remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful evenly onto chicken mixture.
Spread evenly.
Bake uncovered for 30 to 35 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and a dash of pepper.
Shape into 8 oval patties.
Broil over medium coals for 6 minutes. Serve on toasted French bread.

title: nonfat raspberry ice
directions: Sieve the raspberries; discard seeds.
Set berries aside. Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water.
Stir in cold water, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Stir in sieved berries.
Pour mixture into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan and freeze for 3 to 4 hours or until mixture is firm.
Break into chunks and place in a chilled bowl. Beat mixture with an electric mixer until smooth.
Return to loaf pan and freeze about 2 hours or until firm.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Bone and dice chicken.
Melt cheese with the soups.
Mix all ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Pour in casserole dish.
Mix crackers and margarine for topping.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and pineapple together in mixer, then on slow speed mix in vanilla wafers.
Pour this mixture into square dish and spread whipping cream over mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup vanilla wafers and place maraschino cherries on top.
Place in refrigerator at least four hours before serving.

title: crispy oats cookies
directions: Beat butter in large mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg, oil and vanilla, beating well.

title: pear lime mold
directions: Add enough water to the syrup to make 1 cup.
Bring to a boil. Stir into gelatin until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mash pears; beat in cream cheese until smooth and add to thickened gelatin.
Mix well.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups of whipped cream; chill.

title: country casserole
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, cut acorn squash in half; discard seeds.
Cut each acorn squash half into 6 chunks; cut onion into 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Make pudding according to measurements and directions on box. Add Cool Whip and beat with mixer until well blended.
(Remember to add enough milk for 2 boxes.)
Cover bottom of large casserole dish with graham crackers and top with half of pudding mix. Continue layering, ending with graham crackers.
Cover and let set at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.
Ice and serve.

title: dorito chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done and tear into bite size pieces. Lightly grease 13 x 9 pan. Crush Doritos and place 1/2 of the bag in the bottom of dish. Place chicken over Doritos.

title: chipmunk pie
directions: Beat egg and sugar in bowl.
Add salt, flour, vanilla and baking powder; stir in walnuts and apples.
Place in a greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: kathy's almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine and set aside the flour and baking soda.
Combine the Crisco, granulated sugar, dark brown sugar, almond flavoring and water.
Beat until creamy. Beat in the eggs. Gradually add to flour mixture and mix well.
Drop by well rounded half teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass to 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with colored sugar. Bake 6 to 8 minutes.

title: cream puff
directions: Bring to rolling boil water and margarine; add flour.
Keep stirring until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Place on cupboard and add 1 egg at a time (4 eggs total).
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and spread mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: curried salad succotash
directions: Drain liquid from corn and beans into 2 cup measure.
Combine corn, beans, onion, celery, green pepper and pimento in a bowl. Combine 1/2 cup of the vegetable liquid, brown sugar, curry powder, celery seed, salt and vinegar in medium saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, to boiling.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour (or strain, if preferred) over vegetables.
Cool, then chill overnight.

title: cream cheese and fruit mix
directions: Other fruits that can be substituted are frozen strawberries, mandarin oranges and pineapple.

title: peach pie cake
directions: Pour peaches in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Sift cake mix evenly over peaches.
Do not mix. Slice 1 stick butter evenly over cake mix and bake at 350° until brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with butter, nuts and brown sugar that have been mixed together.
Return to oven and bake until topping is slightly crisp.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes at high speed.
Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar.
Stir in the pumpkin and lemon juice.
In a separate bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Fold in the pumpkin mixture.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan which has been well-greased and floured.
Top with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar. Start at narrow end.
Roll towel and cake together.
Cool and unroll.
Beat powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla together. Spread on cake. Roll up like a jelly roll. Chill.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix gently.
Pour into a 1-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until set.
Do not overcook.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions in a bowl.
Add salt.
Cover with water and let stand for 2 or 3 hours.
In deep pot combine vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, turmeric and celery seed.
Drain cucumbers and onions.
Bring solution to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions and cook for about 20 minutes or until pickles change color.
Put in jars and seal.
Let age 3 weeks.

title: hood river sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift 2 tablespoons flour, salt and 3/4 cup of sugar.
Add egg, sour cream, vanilla and nutmeg.
Stir in apples.
Then pour into pastry lined pie pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana snack cake(old-fashioned flavor in this scratch cake.)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine margarine, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Stir in buttermilk, bananas and vanilla; blend thoroughly.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, oats, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in chips.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Sprinkle nuts evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: e-z cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Drop by spoonsful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8-10 minutes at 350.

title: baked pecans
directions: Beat together.
Dip pecans in mixture and lay out on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti delight
directions: Cook spaghetti 10 minutes; drain.
Cook hamburger and drain fat.
Add to hamburger, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, garlic powder and chili pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes, then add cheese, mushrooms and tomato sauce.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook onion in butter over low heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until blended.
Stir in milk.
Return to heat to cook, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove.
Put layer of potatoes, onions and sauce.
Repeat.
Put cheese on top.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts or browns.

title: potato casserole o'brien
directions: Mix together melted margarine and potatoes. Add other ingredients. Bake in a 9 x 13 greased pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Remove core of cabbage and cut head into eighths.
Put enough of the cabbage into the blender to fill halfway.
Add water to cover cabbage.
Coarsely chop.
Empty into strainer to drain thoroughly.
Repeat with remaining cabbage and other vegetables until they are chopped.
Drain very well into a colander.
Place vegetables in bowl.
Put remaining ingredients into container to make the dressing.
Cover.
Blend for 15 seconds.
Pour over chopped vegetables and toss to mix.

title: speedy caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; blend in brown sugar and salt. Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk; continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; blend confectioners sugar gradually.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing well until blended.
Add pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and seasonings.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
You may also roll in minced parsley or shredded dried beef.
Makes 20 to 25 servings.

title: chicken noketele
directions: Brown chicken on both sides.
Brown chopped onion and add to chicken.
Cover with water.
Add paprika and salt.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from pot.
Mix flour into the sour cream and add enough water to make smooth. Add to broth and simmer very slowly until thickened.
Serve on hot buttered noodles; arrange chicken on sides.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients. Stir in bananas and nuts.
Spoon into greased loaf pan and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Wrap in foil while warm.

title: cheese whip pie
directions: Stir together Jell-O and 1/2 cup boiling water until dissolved; add 1/2 cup cold water, stir and set aside to cool, but not jell.

title: hooter's onion bread
directions: Dip biscuits in butter.
Place in 9-inch layer pan.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Top with onion slices.
Brush with remaining butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: kansas city brisket
directions: Place brisket on large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil in large roasting pan.
Sprinkle generously with onion salt, garlic salt and seasoning salt.
Pour liquid smoke over meat.
Seal foil over brisket so that no air can get to meat.
(A drugstore wrap works best.)
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes per pound. Remove from oven and pour off liquid, reserving 1 cup.
Turn side of foil back and pour cup of reserved liquid and 1/2 cup lemon juice over meat.
Add barbecue sauce and cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain. Put in buttered baking dish.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add soup and cheese.
Stir until smooth. Pour over broccoli.
Top with dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: frozen rum cake
directions: Put a thin layer of sponge cake in a refrigerator tray. Sprinkle generously with rum.
Cover with a layer of ice cream. Put another layer of cake on top and sprinkle it with rum.
Leave in freezer to become firm.
Cut into slices to serve.

title: chili con queso potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, sauce, mix and 3 cups boiling water in 3-quart microwavable casserole.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High (100%) 10 minutes.
Stir.
Cover and microwave until potatoes are tender, 7 to 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and microwave until hot, 2 to 4 minutes.

title: rich chocolate pie
directions: Beat butter or margarine and sugar well.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat 5 minutes after each.
Put in baked pie shell and refrigerate.

title: lily's tamale casserole
directions: Coat pan with olive oil.
When oil is hot, add prawns.
Saute until prawns are slightly cooked, adding garlic and pepper. Saute briefly and add vodka.
When flaming stops and juices are reduced, add basil and lemon zest.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions.
Mix rice, broccoli and cream of soup.
Pour into greased (cooking spray) Pyrex dish.
Add can of Cheddar cheese soup (2 if you like it really cheesy).
Mix well.
Place in 375° heated oven.
Bake until slightly brown or bubbly, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh blackberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add sugar mixture to blackberries; toss to coat fruit.
Fill pastry lined 9-inch pie pan with berry mixture.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edge. Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes. Remove foil; bake for 20 to 30 minutes more, or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with next 3 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into molds or loaf pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: holiday chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, except for cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° until heated through.
Do not freeze!!

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve with chips or crackers.

title: dilled vegetable salad
directions: Blanch frozen vegetables in hot water 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and place in glass bowl or large sealable plastic bag.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Boil, drain and refrigerate potatoes.
Grease a casserole dish.
Grate potatoes.
Grate 1/2 pound Cheddar cheese.
(Note: Potatoes should be boiled halfway.)
Mix in dry mustard, nutmeg and salt.
Then pour in milk and whipping cream over potatoes. Sprinkle with onion flakes.
Bake in a 12 x 8-inch dish or larger at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: adult punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Mix well. Then add ice cream.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugars and margarine.
Stir this mixture.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, salt, soda and cocoa.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture; mix well.
Add 1/2 package chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle walnuts and remaining chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This is good with Cool Whip topping.
No frosting required.

title: oreo creme dessert
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or by hand.
Mix cookies with melted margarine.
Reserve 1/4 of mixture to use on topping. Press cookie mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Slice or spread ice cream on top of cookie mixture.
Return to freezer for short period of time until re-frozen.
Spread jar of ice cream sauce on top of ice cream.
Re-freeze again.
Top with frozen topping and sprinkle reserved cookie mixture on Cool Whip. Freeze until ready to serve.
This is always a favorite in the summer!!

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Fill a greased muffin tin 1/2 full. Bake in hot oven.

title: kielbasa surprise
directions: Saute pieces of Kielbasa in butter; add onion and green pepper and continue to saute until done.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: crunchy broccoli
directions: Fry bacon crisp and then crumble.
Mix broccoli flowerettes, dry roasted sunflower seeds and bacon.
Mix dressing (mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar).
Toss salad lightly in dressing.
Refrigerate covered until ready to serve.
Best if made the day it is served.

title: coconut swirls
directions: Melt oleo in 2-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat; add water and vanilla.
Mix powdered sugar and dry milk.
Add to butter mixture about 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition. Stir in coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let stand until firm, about 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips over hot (not boiling) water.
Swirl about 1 teaspoon melted chocolate on each coconut drop.
Chill.
Makes 36.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Shred Velveeta and cheddar cheese into a large bowl.
Add pimentoes, mayonnaise, mustard and salt (if you want it).
Mix until fairly smooth.
Enjoy !

title: fried pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg with milk and add to dry ingredients.
Knead lightly, wrap and chill for 2 hours.
Roll out and fill with fruit.
Fry in oil.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, peanut butter, egg and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in cereal.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, 12 to 13 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Pour 1 1/4 cups boiling
water over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan krispies
directions: Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in foil with seasoning and bake 40 minutes.
Mix
ingredients
and add a little chicken broth, if necessary.
Top
with
onion
rings or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: With an electric mixer, cream margarine, vanilla, eggs and sugar. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add half of the ingredients to the cream mixture and half of the sour cream and beat. Add all the rest of the dry ingredients and the sour cream. Bake 45 minutes in a well-greased tube pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: sweet-sour cabbage(serves 6)
directions: Combine minced onion and 2 tablespoon of water.
Let stand 10 minutes to soften.

title: aunt ruth's toffee
directions: Cook sugar and butter to hard crack stage.
Pour over pecans on a cookie sheet with sides.
Pour chocolate chips on top while still hot.
Spread chocolate over the top with a spatula.

title: granny tyree's strawberry cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 2 greased cake pans and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grate potatoes.
Mix soup, sour cream, chives and cheese together.
Add to grated potatoes and mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
This can be made a day or two ahead or frozen.
Add potato chips and melted butter to top just before you bake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, vanilla, zucchini and nuts.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add this to all the liquid mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Put a layer of cookies in bottom of pan. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over cookies.

title: parmesan stuffed tomatoes
directions: Scoop out pulp; set aside.
Cook onion in margarine.
Stir in pulp, bread crumbs and next 4 ingredients.
Spoon into tomato shells.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and broil for 3 minutes.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass).
In saucepan, melt morsels and butter.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat the cream cheese until fluffy, then beat in sweetened condensed
milk, vanilla and egg.
Pour over crust.
Top with remaining crumbs. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: orange-apricot salad
directions: Bring the sugar and pineapple to a boil.
Add both packages of gelatin.
Remove from the heat and stir in the softened cream cheese.
Mix until the cheese is melted and smooth.
Add ice water and set aside to cool and slightly jell.
Add carrot and celery and fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate until completely set, several hours.

title: meat filled jumbo shells
directions: Cook
jumbo
shells according
to
package
directions, drain. (Cool in a single layer on wax
paper
or foil to keep shells from sticking together.) Brown hamburger and sausage in skillet; drain.
Combine meat, eggs,
bread
crumbs,
cheese, onions, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each
shell with about 2 tablespoons meat filling.
Spread a thin layer
of
sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place the shells,
open side down, in a single layer in the pan.
Cover
with
remaining
sauce. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Fills about 36 shells.

title: apple butter drop cookies
directions: *The
best apple butter in the whole world is made in a small Indiana
village.
I
order
mine from there special and also love their fried biscuits.
Yum!

title: clams casino
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Shuck clams, reserving liquid.
Remove clam and cut into 3 pieces.
Place back on one side of shell. Saute bacon until slightly crisp.
Drain and crumble.

title: hitachi rice
directions: Put all ingredients in hitachi.
Stir 3 times while cooking.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Combine consomme, ketchup, water, onion, green pepper, garlic and oregano in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Add beef; simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve on semi-hard buns.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix barbecue sauce, crushed pineapple and brown sugar in crock-pot.
Add meatballs.
Cook for several hours, until meatballs are done.
When serving, keep crock-pot on low.

title: mississippi mud cake and frosting
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt; add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased oblong pan and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cover baked cake with miniature marshmallows and place back in oven until melted.

title: soda bread
directions: Make a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Form a ball and flatten to about 2-inches high.
Cut a deep cross in it and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, wrap in a damp dish towel until it has cooled.

title: four-layer sugar free dessert
directions: Beat flour and softened oleo.
Add nuts, press into bottom of 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool. Mix softened cream cheese, and 1 cup cool whip thoroughly and spread on cooled crust. Mix 2 pkg. pudding with 3 cups of milk and spread on second layer. Place in refrigerator until set.
Spread cool whip on third layer. If desired, sprinkle with coconut or nuts.
If you use chocolate pudding, it is wise to wait and put fourth layer on just before serving as chocolate may bleed through.

title: copper-cooked chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken, skin sides down, and brown on one side over medium heat.
Cut onions coarsely; add to chicken. Seed and cut pepper coarsely.
Cut tomato coarsely.
Add to skillet; turn chicken.
Add paprika and cook about 10 minutes.
Add water and salt and pepper; reduce heat.
Cover and cook until chicken is tender and vegetables are soft, about 25 minutes total cooking time.
Stir in sour cream.
Do not boil.
Warm and serve.

title: layered brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Combine remaining ingredients except chocolate chips in a large bowl.
Mix by hand until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of the dough into pan, reserving the rest for topping.
Bake dough 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture over chocolate chips. Sprinkle remaining dough on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cucumber smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: southern hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add crushed potato chips on top.
Melt margarine, pour over potatoes and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: treasure chest bars
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together the brown sugar, white sugar and butter.
Blend in the unbeaten eggs.
Beat well after each egg.
Add the vanilla; beat until fluffy, then add flour mixture with 3/4 cup milk.
Begin and end with flour.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in the nuts, cherries and chocolate chips.
Grease and flour bottom of jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: crab potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Halve them.
Scoop out and mash potatoes while still hot, adding first the butter, then other ingredients and mix well.
Re-fill potato skins (or put into seashells) and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Can be made in advance.
Serves 12.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 3 layer pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: macaroni shrimp salad
directions: Mix ingredients and add 1 pound cooked shrimp just before serving.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; set aside.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain off excess fat.
Heat Ro-Tel tomatoes until hot; add cheese and heat until melted.
Add chili powder and cooked sausage.
Serve with chips.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover melted margarine with crackers, coconut, then chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour milk over it and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry or peach fruit punch
directions: If you are going to make a mold, you may add cherries, strawberries or orange slices to decorate mold.
Pour 1 bottle of soda in mold and freeze overnight.
Bring water and sugar to a boil, then let cool completely.
Stir all ingredients together and serve very cold.

title: rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in warm water.
Melt margarine, then add milk and heat until lukewarm. Mix all ingredients, adding flour last (all-purpose). It makes a fairly stiff dough.
Place on floured surface and knead, then put in an oiled bowl.
Let rise 1 hour. Pinch off in balls or roll out and cut on lightly floured board. Put in a well-greased pan.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles, drain and let cool.
Then mix onion, green pepper, and 8 oz. Italian dressing, mix well.
Add salad supreme. Mix and ready to serve.

title: brownies from scratch
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and mix well. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This can easily be doubled if you're having a huge "brownie attack!"

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Drop by rounded balls into frypan in which 1/4-inch of oil has been preheated.
Fry until crisp and brown on both sides.

title: gudbrandsdalkaker
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Add rest of ingredients in order, blending after each addition.
This is a drop cookie and should not be larger than a half-dollar.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Place chicken in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Beat eggs; blend in milk, salt, pepper and mace.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle shredded cheese, Parmesan cheese and paprika over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: the family fudge(since the 1800's)
directions: Bring sugar and milk to boil, stirring well.
Reduce heat just to maintain a good bubbling boil for 7 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Stir to cool slightly before adding vanilla. Beat lustily until thickening begins and texture becomes smooth. Pour into buttered 8-inch pie pan.
Mark and cut when set.

title: heavenly pumpkin pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Cook pumpkin, milk, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and spice over boiling water for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in gelatin.
Chill until thick. Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Beat egg white until stiff, adding remaining sugar gradually.
Fold pumpkin, vanilla, 1 cup Dream Whip into egg whites.
Pour in shell.
Chill.
Top with Dream Whip.

title: pasta and fresh vegetables
directions: Saute garlic in margarine in large skillet for 3 minutes. Stir in flour until well mixed.
Add hot pepper sauce, broth and lemon juice gradually, stirring well after each addition.
Cook until sauce thickens, stirring constantly.
Cook noodles using package directions; drain.
Combine noodles, broccoli and carrots in serving dish.
Pour sauce over vegetables.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar 10 minutes at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat flour, baking powder, salt and milk for 1 minute.
Pour in floured and greased cake pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: vincent's soup
directions: Cook rice. Brown meat and add taco seasoning. Steam carrots, broccoli and onions. Drain beans. Mix all ingredients together. Heat and serve over tortilla chips.

title: granny's beef stew
directions: Brown beef by first covering with flour and then cooking in oil (approximately 1/2 cup).
Add onion.
When beef is browned and onion glossy, add enough water to pot to fill 3/4 full.
Add potatoes, carrots and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Then simmer for approximately 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Before serving, add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: grandma's easy overnight yeast rolls
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs and salt. Beat together. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add yeast/water mixture and flour. Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook over low heat until it starts to thicken.
Pour over layers of wafers and bananas.

title: apricot-sauced pork chops
directions: Place chops on unheated broiler pan.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 20 minutes, or until pork is no longer pink and is well done, turning once.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Put 3/4 cup of stuffing in greased casserole.
Alternate string beans, chicken and almonds.
Combine milk and soup; pour over ingredients.
Cover with remaining stuffing.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in 1/4 cup hot water and pour over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: squizzill
directions: Put browned beef in casserole.
Pour soup over beef.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel and mash.
Add butter, sugar, nutmeg and salt.
Beat until creamy.
When cool, beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.

title: dang good pie
directions: Blend sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add pineapple, coconut, flour, and vanilla.
Stir and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes then 350° for 45 minutes.
May need to cover crust to prevent over browning.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix oats, coconut, cocoa and salt in medium bowl.
Set aside. In saucepan, put margarine, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.
Leave there until set.

title: amish cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together and stir in milk.
Cut margarine into little pieces and add to mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in preheated 325° oven.

title: a bit-o-honey shake
directions: Put ice cream into blender; add milk, peanut butter, vanilla and honey.
Blend on high speed until thick and smooth.
Pour into 1 large glass or 2 small glasses and serve immediately.
Good after school snack.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Put a well in the center of mixture. Add eggs, buttermilk and oil; stir well. Cover and store in refrigerator.
Will last 4 to 6 weeks. Spoon batter into muffin tins. Fill 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vichyssoise-potato soup
directions: Cover chicken parts completely with water.
Bring to rolling boil, 5 minutes.
Simmer until tender.
Cool.
Pick meat from bones.
Strain broth.
In another container, add all ingredients to broth; add additional canned broth if needed.
Bring to rolling boil.
Simmer until tender.
Add chicken pieces.
Serve cold with French bread or hot with corn bread.

title: lemon supreme
directions: Combine butter, flour and nuts in small bowl.
Mix like pie dough (soft).
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread thin and put small curl up side of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: alaska recipe - russian tea
directions: Shake together in a bag or large can.
Store in a tight jar. To serve, dissolve a heaping teaspoonful of mixture in 1 cup of hot water.
Drink and enjoy.

title: creamy cheese bars
directions: Mix the cream cheese and brown sugar; spread on crust.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until crust is brown and cheese sets.

title: caramel for apples
directions: Cook slowly on medium heat the condensed milk, sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Stir constantly and gently.
Cook to 230° on candy thermometer.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Turns brown as it cooks. Burns easily!
Takes about 15 minutes to ready 230° on candy thermometer.

title: laura's pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a large stock pot.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add more water if soup becomes too thick.
Puree the vegetables or leave as is.
Either way is delicious.
Serve with croutons.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine diced apples, Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts in serving dish. Mix sugar, flour, gelatine, pineapple juice and egg in a saucepan. Cook slowly until it boils and thickens. Cool completely. When cool, pour the sauce over the apples, Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate. Best if made the night before.

title: marie's gala rainbow cake
directions: Split an angel food cake into 4 layers.
Whip cream with confectioners sugar until stiff.
Combine pineapple with 1/2 cup whipped cream.
Combine mashed apricots with 1/2 cup whipped cream.
Combine jam with 1/2 cup whipped cream.
Spread one filling on each layer.
Use the rest of the whipped cream to frost the cake.
Decorate with chopped nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate 12 hours before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mash strawberries very fine.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix all ingredients.
Makes 3 layers or good size Bundt cake.

title: sauerkraut and meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, soup and eggs together. Shape into small meatballs. Place in a 9 x 13 pan. Cover with sauerkraut. Mix together the rest of ingredients and heat to dissolve cranberry sauce a little. Spoon mixture over sauerkraut and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: quick crab casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in 1 stick oleo until tender; add crabmeat. Soak bread in enough milk to soften completely.
Break into pieces and add to crab mixture.
Stir well and add seasonings.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove meat from bones and chop.
Mix chicken meat, soup, sour cream and chiles. Heat oil in a small frypan.
Dip each tortilla into the hot oil until softened.
Drain on towels.

title: blueberry or fruit pie
directions: Sprinkle fruit with lemon juice. Set aside. Fit half of pastry in a 9-inch pie plate according to package directions. Combine 1 cup sugar and next 3 ingredients. Add to fruit, stirring well. Pour into pastry shell and dot with butter. Unfold remaining pastry on a lightly floured surface. Roll out to remove creases. Place pastry over filling. Seal and crimp edges. Cut slits in top of crust. Brush top of pastry with beaten egg and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until golden brown. Cover edges with aluminum foil to prevent overbrowning.

title: lamb roast
directions: Put lamb in pan.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Add soup.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together cake mix, pie filling and eggs in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Combine sugar and cinnamon.

title: oven barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs in serving-size pieces. In large saucepan, cover ribs with salted water. Cover and simmer until nearly tender, about 1 hour.

title: springtime salad
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Cut flowerets into pieces.
chop broccoli.
Combine cauliflower, broccoli, onion, bacon and cheese.

title: gary's mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, pepper and onion.
Drain.
Line bottom of casserole dish with corn chips and pour the hamburger mixture over the chips.
Cover this with half of the grated cheese.
Combine tomatoes and pepper, pinto beans and mushroom soup.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and the remaining bag of crushed corn chips on top.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: quick stroganoff
directions: Heat some oil in a skillet, add beef and vegetables and cook until browned and juices evaporate, stirring often.
Add soup, broth, water, worcestershire sauce and pasta.
Heat to boil.
Cook over medium heat 15 minutes or until done, stirring.
Add sour cream.
Heat through.
(Serves 4.)

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt.
Bring mixture to a boil; boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats and spoon onto wax paper.

title: chocolate scotcharoos
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup; heat until bubbles form around the edge of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Stir in cereal.
Press mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: too-easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place fruit in butter in 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Cut crusts from bread slices and cut each slice into 5 fingers. Place the bread fingers over the fruit. In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and butter. Pour over fruit and bread. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, until golden. Serves 5 to 6.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix and store in jar.
Add 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water. Keeps indefinitely.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain excess oil.
Add chili beans, tomato juice and tomatoes.
Add spices to taste.
Simmer several hours.

title: fritters
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat milk and egg; add to flour mixture.
Add vanilla and mix.
Drop by tablespoon
into deep, hot oil for 2 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with hot syrup.

title: grated broccoli with parmesan
directions: Peel and grate the broccoli stems.
Shred the cheese.
Heat the oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.
Add the grated broccoli stems and 3/4 teaspoon salt and toss to coat.
Cover, reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in red pepper flakes and cook 1 minute.
Stir in the Parmesan cheese and serve.
Serves 6, 128 calories per serving.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill about 3 hours until set. Top with pie filling.

title: french toast(kid recipe)
directions: Mix eggs, milk and salt.
Cut bread slices in half.
Heat a lightly greased skillet or griddle.
Pick up bread with a fork and dip both sides into egg mixture.
Place bread onto hot griddle. Brown on both sides.
Turn bread with spatula.
Serve hot. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Top with margarine and favorite syrup.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside 1/2 cup.
Mix remaining crumbs with butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 container of whipped topping. Spread over cookie crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Prepare pudding mix by directions on package.
Spread over cheese mixture. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg in a large bowl. Stir in milk, corn meal and 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add and beat in flour, baking powder, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Drop tablespoons of the mixture into deep or shallow hot oil (375°).
Fry until golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Serve with a syrup, if desired.
Makes about 4 fritters per person.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mom's cole slaw
directions: Mix vegetables in bowl.

title: crispy chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in 2 pieces.
Discard tips.
In small shallow bowl, combine butter and garlic powder.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Dip chicken into butter mixture, then into crumb mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Makes about 20 wings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cornbread
and
stick of margarine.
Put 1/4 to 1/2 in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together squash, bell pepper and onion.
Add
sour
cream and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over cornbread. Add remaining cornbread over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Cook
cauliflower
rosettes
in simmering, salted water until done.
Stir
soup,
cheese,
mayonnaise, curry and nuts together. Place
in
quart casserole.
Add cauliflower and mix well. Toss bread crumbs in margarine and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Add water to taste.

title: candy
directions: Melt chocolate in 200° oven.
Add all ingredients to chocolate; mix and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: goody bars(great)
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter.
Pat mixture in bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar together.
Spread over other mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift 2 cups of flour and powdered sugar together.
Cut in margarine.
Press into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix with enough mayonnaise to moisten. Maybe enough pickle juice to taste. Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste. Serve on lettuce leaf or alone with crackers (Ritz, etc.).

title: crispy cookie coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in oleo and add vanilla.
Combine eggs, milk and dissolved yeast and add to flour mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar, flavoring and Carnation milk.
Mix together.
Put mixture into ice cream churn and then add 1/2 gallon of milk.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into florets.
Slice onion into rings.
Mix broccoli, onion and raisins.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. Pour over broccoli mixture.
Refrigerate about 2 hours or overnight.
Fry bacon and crumble over top of salad when ready to serve.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add cocoa, water, vanilla and rolled oats, blending well.
Chill.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 3 dozen.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk for 1 minute.
Then add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: cube steak
directions: Flour both sides of each steak.
Fry in a small amount of oil until brown.
Place steaks in large oval baking dish.
Mix 1 package of Lipton beefy mushroom (Recipe Secrets) with 2 1/2 cups of water.
Pour over steaks.
Bake at 350 until nice and tender, approx. 1 1/2 hours).

title: batter bread(baked in a coffee can)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a large mixer bowl.
Blend in 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let stand in a warm place for 15 minutes.
Stir in remaining 2 tablespoons sugar and the milk, salt and the oil. With mixer on low speed, beat in the flour 1 cup at a time, beating very well after each addition.
Beat in last cup of flour with a heavy spoon; add flour until dough is very heavy and stiff but still sticky.
Place dough in 2 well-greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Cover with well-greased lids.
(Freeze if you wish.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and oleo.
Cook rice as directed.
Mix everything and put in pre-sprayed dish (9 x 13-inch).
Top with seasoned bread crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake in oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Prepare cake using package directions for oblong cake.
Pierce top of hot cake.
Pour next 2 ingredients over top.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Spread with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Shake chicken in bag with flour, garlic powder, salt, pepper and Cajun seasoning.
Whip egg whites in medium bowl until slightly frothy.
Dip rolled chicken in egg, then into crushed cornflakes.
Bake on oiled baking sheet at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown and done in center.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Place chicken on bottom of 8 x 10 pan. Combine soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers. Crumble over mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix water, yeast, sugar and Crisco in a separate bowl; to separate bowl, add soda and buttermilk.
Then add this to water mixture.
Add flour and beat well.
Refrigerate, tightly covered, for 2 hours.
Use as needed.
(Do not knead dough.)
Can be used up to 1 week.

title: sirloin tips and mushrooms
directions: In a wide skillet, brown meat in 2 tablespoons of the butter and the oil, and garlic.
As the pieces brown, remove them to a casserole dish with a cover.
Add remaining butter to the skillet and saute the mushrooms, then add to meat.
Cover and bake slowly at 275 degrees for 1 hour or until the meat is tender.
Meanwhile add broth, wine, and soy sauce to the skillet.
Boil, making sure to scrap up the browning at the bottom of the skillet.
Let this reduce to a glaze and then blend in the mustard, cornstarch, and cream.
Bring to boil until thick.
Pour off the juices from in the meat/mushrooms into the sauce in the skillet whisking until smooth and thick.
Add sauce to meat and top with chopped parsley.
Serve.

title: really good sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Serve over buns (toasted).

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice tenderloin almost all the way to the end and lay top part back.
Saute in butter, onion, peppers and canned mushrooms; when almost done, add vegetables to middle of tenderloin.
Fold top back over vegetables and bake, uncovered, for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
I use a meat thermometer.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop vegetables. Add all ingredients. Cook 35 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt millie's pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Add to sugar and shortening mix.
Stir in crushed pineapple and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls and bake at 375° until browned.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: slaw
directions: Mix together and pour over cabbage. Toss lightly to coat all the vegetables.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine milk, thawed lemonade and softened Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples and slice each apple into 5 sections.
Separate each biscuit into 3 layers. Wrap each slice of apple with 1 layer of biscuit.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish. Boil the water, sugar and margarine. After bringing to a boil, pour over apples and biscuits and sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Put in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix and heat in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix margarine and cocoa in saucepan.
Cool after well blended.
Beat eggs in separate bowl and add cocoa mixture.
Add sugar, flour, flavoring and salt and mix well.
Add nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: citrus salad
directions: In small bowl combine sour cream, honey and grated orange peel; chill until ready to serve.
Arrange lettuce, grapefruit and oranges decoratively on serving platter.
Sprinkle with chopped onion.
Serve with chilled sour cream dressing.
Makes 12 servings.

title: ham sandwiches
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Brush mixture onto both sides of bun.
Then add layer of cheese, ham and cheese.
Brush top of bun with butter mixture.

title: judy's 1000 island relish
directions: Chop cucumbers and cauliflower, peel and chop onions, and seed and chop sweet peppers.
Mix salt and vegetables and let stand for one hour.
Drain liquid.
Mix spices, sugar, and flour in large kettle.
Moisten with water, add vinegar and drained vegetables.
Cook 20-30 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Seal at once. Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 10 pints.

title: curry chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a baking dish.
Mix honey, mustard, butter and curry powder together.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes until done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spanish rice
directions: In heavy skillet over medium heat, add 2 tablespoons shortening.
Add 1 cup uncooked rice and brown, stirring constantly until golden brown.
Add chopped onion, tomatoes and juice, water and salt to taste or 1 teaspoon.
Bring to a full boil; cover tightly.
Turn down heat to simmer and cook slowly until rice has absorbed most of the water and is tender.
Add 1 can of peas and heat through.
Serves 8.

title: potato stuffed franks
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed on box and mix with onions, parsley and mustard. Split franks lengthwise not cutting clear through. Place opened, cut side up, on rack in broiler pan. Spread with potato mix; sprinkle with cheese.
Place in oven; set to broil about 5 inches from broiler unit. Heat until cheese is melted, about 5 to 8 minutes.

title: hawaiian noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain well. Melt margarine.
Beat eggs.
Add melted margarine, sugar and baking powder; mix well.
Add coconut, pineapple and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Add noodles and mix well.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar; boil for 5 minutes. Add Jell-O and boil for 5 to 8 minutes longer. Put in jars. Keep in refrigerator. Makes 2 pints.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits. Mix in bowl with coconut and sour cream.
Stir in marshmallows until sour cream covers everything.
Refrigerate for an hour or more before serving.

title: pork chop spanish rice
directions: *Substitute 1 pound 12 ounce can tomatoes, 1 teaspoon chili powder and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream the peanut butter, Crisco and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Add baking powder and salt to flour. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add milk and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for almost 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool completely, then put icing on cake.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together and put in large mixing bowl. Put butter, Crisco, cocoa and water in saucepan. Bring this to a rapid boil and pour over flour and sugar mix. Stir well. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake 20 minutes. Use frosting of your choice.

title: good morning pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls onto round (greased) pizza pan.
Add sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together; pour over top. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°, or until brown.

title: dip for strawberries or fruit
directions: Mix sour cream, brown sugar, almond extract and almonds together until well blended. Refrigerate.
Use as dip with strawberries and/or other fruit.
Can top dessert dish of strawberries with dollop of cream mixture and garnish with toasted almonds.

title: cocktail franks
directions: Brown onion.
Add grape jelly; blend well.
Add chili sauce; simmer with franks for about 30 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crust.
Put in freezer for several hours.
Remove from freezer about 10 minutes before serving.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let marinate overnight.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over cut up dates; let stand 20 minutes. Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 small loaves.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Brown beef in Dutch oven.
Add all ingredients to beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: elise's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream
together,
sugar, Crisco and peanut butter.
Add eggs, then
flour
and
soda,
sifted
together.	Make
a good dough. Pinch
off small pieces.
Roll into balls and place on a cookie sheet.
With
a wet fork, press down on balls crisscross.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes (ovens vary).
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute cabbage, onion and green pepper with butter until onion appears clear.
Add soup and salt, mixing well.
Pour into greased baking dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ground beef and cabbage main course
directions: Brown meat, onions and seasonings until meat is cooked.
Add chopped cabbage.
Cover with sauce and water.
Simmer with lid on until cabbage is tender.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar.
When Jello has cooled add all the other ingredients and mix well.
Place in mold until jelled. Can be frozen, also.

title: mustard short ribs
directions: Place beef ribs in shallow, glass dish.
Mix mustard, sugar, lemon juice, salt, pepper and garlic.
Spread over beef.
Top with onions.
Cover and refrigerate, turning beef occasionally for 24 hours.
Cook beef in 4-quart Dutch oven over medium heat until brown; drain.
Add onions and pour marinade over beef.
Cover and cook in 350° oven until tender, about 2 hours.

title: cheese dip
directions: In your crock-pot, melt cheese, Ro-Tel and cream of mushroom soup.
Brown ground beef and mix with sauce.
Simmer and serve. Best with Fritos corn chips scoops.

title: oreo pudding
directions: Whip topping; add to softened cream cheese.
Mix pudding with milk.
Beat these 2 together.
Crush cookies.
Put half in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pudding mixture over cookies; top with remaining cookie crumbs.
Enjoy!

title: refrigerator icing
directions: Beat eggs in one at a time.
The more you beat the better. Store the frosted cake in the refrigerator.

title: best cake ever
directions: Pour all ingredients except nuts in bowl and mix well. Add chopped nuts quickly. Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: spice tea
directions: Combine Tang, sugar, tea, spices and salt.
Store in tightly covered jar.
Each serving: 1 well rounded teaspoon of mix in cup. Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Serve.

title: shrimp oriental salad
directions: In large pan, mix vinegar, lime juice, honey, ginger, garlic, soy sauce and red pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1/3 of shrimp; cook quickly (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove with slotted spoon.
Cook rest of shrimp, 1/3 at a time.
Reserve liquid; cover and refrigerate until next day.
Mix with the rest of ingredients and serve.
Can add sesame seed or walnuts.
Serve with sesame bread and mineral water.

title: mexi-chili casserole
directions: Reserve 1 cup corn chips and 1/2 cup cheese.
Combine remaining chips and cheese with all ingredients, except sour cream in bowl; mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with sour cream.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese. Arrange remaining corn chips around edge.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix in	order.	Bake in an ungreased pan for 20 minutes on 350°. For larger batch, double the ingredients.

title: pecan roll
directions: Chop nuts; mix with 3/4 graham crackers and milk in double boiler.
Cut marshmallows and melt.
Pour over mixture; mix. Crumble remainder of graham crackers.
Pour mixture over crackers and roll.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Let vanilla ice cream partially thaw, then mix with Cool Whip and crushed Oreos.
Put into a 9x13-inch pan and freeze.

title: confetti potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Combine potatoes, green onions, green pepper, celery, carrots and eggs in large bowl.
Combine dressing, sour cream and lemon juice; stir well.
Add dressing to vegetable mixture, tossing gently.
Sprinkle with paprika.
It is best if made the day before you wish to serve it.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and pour into graham cracker crust; freeze.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Put chicken boiling.
When the water and chicken have boiled for about 15 minutes, put roux, onions and seasoning and cook until done.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water until smooth.
Stir egg yolks, bring to a boil over medium heat.
Spoon hot filling into crust.

title: lemon salad
directions: Blend Jell-O, sugar and salt.
Add boiling water and stir until completely dissolved.
Stir in lemonade.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill until firm.
Can be molded.
Also good with lime Jell-O and limeade concentrate.

title: hungarian pastry
directions: Cream oleo
and
sugar; add rest of the ingredients and knead well.
Press
on
ungreased lipped cookie sheet.
Spread on top 2 cans
pie
filling.
(We like cherry best.) Top with meringue.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Soak bread in milk, tear into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas king ranch chicken
directions: Crush Doritos fine.
Line buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish with half of the Doritos.
Do not use smaller, deeper dish.
Mix well both soups, Ro-Tel and Pet milk.
Place half of this mixture on top of crushed Doritos.
Next, add half of other ingredients in the following order:
chicken, onion, green peppers and grated cheese.
Repeat this same procedure.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix flour, butter, nuts and white sugar.
Press in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool, crumble and pat in pan.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; stir in cheeses. Store in refrigerator up to 1 week. Yield: 4 cups. Preparation time: 15 min.

title: anise cookies
directions: Beat eggs with electric beater for 10 minutes.
Gradually add sugar and flour which has been sifted with baking powder.
Add anise oil.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered baking sheets. Sprinkle with candy beads.
Let dry at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips in microwave then add milk and vanilla.
Stir and add peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: italian flavored grilled chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a plastic bowl with cover.
Pour Italian dressing and Worcestershire sauce over chicken.
Marinate the chicken for 2 to 3 hours.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat and slice beef in thin, bite-sized pieces.
Coat with ginger, salt, black pepper and garlic powder.
Saute in oil until brown.
Remove beef.
Saute chopped green peppers and chopped onions.
Add broth, water, soy sauce, beef and water chestnuts. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cornstarch, dissolved in cold water to thicken.
Pour over cooked rice.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain cherries.
Heat cherry juice and dissolve jello in hot juice.
Cool.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: sausage gravy
directions: In skillet, put lard or Crisco and crumble up the sausage. Fry on medium until sausage is brown.
Pour out all grease, except for about 3 tablespoons.
Leave sausage in pan.
Add flour and brown.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Keep stirring until gravy is thick.
If too thick, add some hot water.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Continue cooking for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: herbed tomato chicken
directions: In skillet, combine onions, garlic and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boiling.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until onion is tender. Drain.
Add chicken to skillet.
Combine undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, green pepper, basil, salt, bay leaf and dash of pepper.
Pour over chicken, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in wine and cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes more.
Remove bay leaf. Skim excess fat from juices.
Transfer chicken and sauce to serving platter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pittzells
directions: Put a little oil on pittzell iron.
Use towel to soak up excess.
Add 1 to 2 shots of whiskey.
Press down 30 seconds (keep checking).

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Add melted margarine.
Pour into pie shell, unbaked.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: magic rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Layer hash browns and mix.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Pour margarine over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion sticks
directions: Mix all but onion rings.
Make crescent rolls into 4 rectangles (press edges of 2 triangles together).
Cut each rectangle into 8 strips.
Dip in egg mixture and roll in crushed onions.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
One can = 32 sticks.

title: cherry surprises
directions: Melt
margarine.
Mix
with crumbs. Spread half of this into a Pyrex dish.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk together. Pour
this	on
top
of
crumbs.
Pour
cherry
pie filling on top
of
this.
Beat Dream Whip and pour on top of cherries, then sprinkle on remaining crumbs.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers; remove stems and seeds.
Leave whole or cut in half and scald in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Cook hamburger and onion until brown.
Drain and stir in salt, garlic salt, cooked rice and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Stuff peppers and place in baking pan with just enough water to cover bottom (about 2 tablespoons).
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until peppers are tender.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda and baking powder.
Cream sugar until well blended but not fluffy.
Add eggs, margarine, butter and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour.
Knead in bowl only long enough to form a smooth dough.
Divide in 4 parts and roll each part into a roll about 1 inch in diameter.
Cut in 1-inch lengths.
Roll pieces in palm of hands to form smooth balls.
Lay on ungreased cookie sheets, 1 inch apart.
Press with tines of fork to make crisscross.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: coconut mocha drops(microwave time: about 2 minutes; stand time: 15 minutes)
directions: Mix coffee, margarine and milk in large bowl.
Cover loosely and microwave on High 1 minute and 30 seconds to 2 minutes or until margarine is almost melted and mixture is hot.
Stir until coffee is dissolved.
Stir in powdered sugar until smooth.
Stir in coconut.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls into waxed paper.
Let stand 15 minutes or until firm.
Makes about 4 dozen candies, 55 calories per candy.

title: holiday broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until tender about 8 to 10 minutes. Drain. Blend soup and mayonnaise.
Place in 1 1/2 quart casserole. Squeeze lemon over broccoli.
Cover with soup, top with bread crumbs and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters on paper towel.
Roll oysters in cracker crumbs, dip into egg and again in cracker crumbs.
Place in wire basket and fry in deep hot oil until brown and crisp.
Do not overcook.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Make 3 holes in your dry mixture.
Put oil, vinegar and vanilla in each separate hole.
Pour cold water over top.
Mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If you want to double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan, 12 tablespoons equals 3/4 cup.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes together in a large bowl. Fold in the potatoes until all of the potatoes are evenly coated. As a final touch, sprinkle paprika on top.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: brunch for a bunch
directions: Place hash browns in pan; salt lightly.
Brown sausage and drain.
Place over potatoes.
Put pepper and cheese over sausage. Beat eggs; add milk and a little salt.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pickled squash
directions: Mix squash and salt; let set 1 hour (drain).
Bring sugar, vinegar and spices to a boil.
Add the squash to the boiling vinegar.
Bring to a boil again.
Let boil for 10 to 15 minutes. Put into hot jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger and diced onion until done.
Add kidney beans and taco seasoning, cool.
Mix in diced tomatoes, shredded lettuce and cheese.
Add dressing, recipe follows.
Break up chips and mix into bowl.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased baking dish.

title: congealed salad (dessert)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sit in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours.
Ready to eat.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Arrange banana slices on bottom of pie crust.
Set aside. Pour milk
into medium bowl. Add pudding and beat until well blended.
Pour mixture at once into pie crust. Cover with chocolate Cool Whip, partially overlapping to edge of crust. Arrange banana slices on top of Cool Whip forming a single ring around topping. Chill.

title: pot roast with tomato gravy
directions: Brown roast in 1/4 cup oil in Dutch oven. Add garlic, thyme, vinegar, salt, pepper and 1/3 cup water. Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours. Add tomatoes; simmer for about 1 hour longer or until roast is tender. Remove roast to hot plate.
Remove garlic and discard.
Mix flour with 1/4 cup water. Stir into tomato mixture. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Pour over noodles. Serve with roast.

title: stuffed sweet onions
directions: Cut a slice from the top of each onion; scoop out the centers, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells.
Reserve centers for other uses. Place shells in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Combine peas, mushrooms and the next 2 ingredients; spoon evenly into onions and dot with butter.
Combine water and bouillon granules; pour over stuffed onions.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small corner of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 7 to 9 minutes, giving dish a half turn after 4 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter, in top of double boiler. Do not let water in bottom boil.
Beat well, over moderate heat. Add butter and keep beating until sauce is rich and thick.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar, eggs, shortening, vanilla, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add flour alternately with sour milk.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes in greased loaf pan, 6 x 10-inch.

title: iceberg pickles
directions: 1st Day:
Put cukes in 3-gallon crock (whole).
Pour 1 gallon of boiling water over them.
Let stand 24 hours.
Repeat this the 2nd, 3rd and 4th days.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve the jello in 4 cups boiling water.
Add 9 cups cold water, sugar, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Stir well.
Freeze in gallon milk jugs.
When ready to use, pour 1/2 gallon ginger ale and 7-Up.

title: peach strudel
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Fill baking dish 3/4 full of sliced peaches.
Cover with 1/2 cup sugar and pour batter over.
Bake 1/2 hour in 350° oven.
Serve topped with ice cream.

title: poor man's supper
directions: Put all beans into crock-pot with onion.
Season with a slice of country ham, cut into pieces.
Cook over night or 8 hours. Serve with coleslaw and corn bread for a "Poor Man's Supper."

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a mixing bowl.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese (4 ounces), sour cream, salt and pepper. Mix until fluffy.
Place in a well-buttered 1 1/2-quart rectangular baking dish and sprinkle the top with canned French fried onions.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until well heated. Serves 4 to 6.

title: crockpot chili
directions: Cook ground chuck, drain fat.
Combine all ingredients in a slow cooker/Crock Pot and cook 4 to 6 hours on low, or until done.

title: kahlua truffle
directions: Mix pudding with half and half; set aside.
Sprinkle cake cubes evenly with Kahlua.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Mix pudding and cake cubes together.

title: grilled salmon
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in Ziploc bag with fish.
Seal; marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Prepare grill or broiler pan with cooking spray.
Cook 5 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork, basting with reserved marinade.
Place remaining marinade in a saucepan.
Bring to boil. Serve with fish.
Garnish with green onions and lemon slices.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in chicken, 1/2 cup picante sauce and cumin; heat.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 cup cheese.
Spoon about 1/3 cup chicken mixture down the center of each tortilla; roll.
Place seam side down in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining picante sauce over enchiladas; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with onions and sour cream.

title: nutty cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans; chill until able to shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts; garnish with halves.
Chill. Serve with crackers.
Can make individual small balls and insert pretzel sticks.

title: salt rising bread
directions: Mix together cornmeal, salt, sugar and soda. Take 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 cup boiling water and mix together; pour over meal mixture. Let stand in warm spot overnight. It should be bubbly the next morning. If not discard and begin again.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salted water for about 45 minutes. Cut into 1/2 to 1-inch pieces.
Cook broccoli; drain.
In baking dish, spread broccoli, then layer chicken on top.
Mix the Miracle Whip, soup, curry powder and lemon juice; pour over chicken. Sprinkle 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese over chicken.
Melt 2 teaspoons margarine; mix with 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese. (May use Ritz crackers.)
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, blend together the first 5 ingredients.
Add milk; cook and stir until it boils. Stir in vegetables and turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Preparation time: 10 minutes; cooking time: 30 minutes.
Easy.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugars and margarine. Stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add flour to sugar mixture; mix well.
Add about half of the package of chocolate chips.

title: spinach hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into bite size balls. Bake in 350° oven, about 20 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated at later time.

title: red grape salad
directions: Wash and dry grapes. Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and vanilla. Add to grapes and place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Spread on brown sugar and walnuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until a golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with seafood.

title: turkey sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, saute ground turkey, onion and bell pepper 5 minutes or until turkey is no longer pink.
Add catsup, relish, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt, garlic powder and celery seed.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 to 3/4 can of water and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: hearty vegetable beef barley soup
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown in 2 tablespoons of oil with garlic.
Drain, if needed.
Add tomatoes, water, barley, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon, basil and pepper.
Bring to a boil; simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil; simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grandma greiner's spice cake
directions: Boil the first 8 ingredients for 3 minutes and cool.
(This takes a long time.
I often do it one night and do the rest the next day.)

title: pineapple peach delight (pie)
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice until thick, then add other ingredients and pour into a graham cracker crumb or vanilla wafer crumb crust.

title: marinated hot dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat.
Cut hot dogs in 1/2-inch size pieces and simmer for 20 minutes.
May double or triple recipe.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Defrost broccoli, cook as directed on package and strain. Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add cheese, milk and seasoning to taste. Combine all ingredients.
Bake in oven at 400°.
Check after 25 minutes.

title: pastor griffin's eastern shore fried egg sandwich
directions: Place lard in iron skillet over medium heat.
When hot, crack eggs and carefully place in hot grease.
When egg whites are firm, turn eggs over and sprinkle (to taste) with Old Bay seasoning. Cook only until yolk is not runny, then place on hot buttered bread and enjoy immediately!

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water (110°) or compressed yeast in lukewarm water (85°).
Add sugar, salt and about half the flour.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes.
Add egg and oil.
Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover with a damp cloth and waxed paper.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together first 9 ingredients and top with cracker crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well.
