Mix remaining ingredients and pour into well.
Stir enough to dampen all ingredients and pour into two loaf pans, greased, floured and lined with wax paper. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 2 tablespoons liquid.
In mixing bowl, combine salmon, egg and onion; stir in flour.
Combine baking powder and reserved liquid.
Stir into salmon mixture.
Form in small patties and fry.

title: shrimp fra diavolo
directions: Saute shrimp and garlic in olive oil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Serve mixture on a bed of rice and topped with chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs, margarine and powdered sugar; put in pan.
Mix together egg, cream cheese, granulated sugar, vanilla and cherry pie filling.
Put into pan on top of first mixture. Top with Dream Whip.

title: hot salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs.
Add vinegar and water slowly.
Pour in pan with fried bacon.
Cook.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise and mustard.

title: spiked punch
directions: Mix frozen juices with water as directed on cans.
Add 7-Up and Southern Comfort when ready to serve.

title: the real deal old-timey pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add small amounts of the beaten eggs alternately with small amounts flour; mix just until blended.
Add enough flavoring extract of your choice to suit your taste.
Bake in a well greased bundt pan at 300 degrees for 2 hours without opening the oven door.
Serve warm with fat free cool whip.

title: fried rice
directions: Put oil in skillet.
Let it get hot.
Saute the garlic until brown, then put in the meat.
Stir until cooked.
Then add soy sauce and seasoning.
Stir again.
Wait a few minutes, then put all the vegetables, except green onion, in.
When the meat and vegetables cook, mix in the rice.
Separate the eggs.
Scramble the eggs.
Put a little salt and seasoning in.
Slice the green onion. On top of fried rice, put green onion first and then the egg.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix in order given. Roll or pat out and cut with biscuit cutter. Place on greased cookie sheet and fold in half.
Bake at medium heat until light golden brown. (Does not need to rise before baking.) Dough can be stored in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: mom's apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Batter will be thick.
Bake in 9 x 14-inch pan for 75 minutes at 350°.

title: layered taco bean dip
directions: Combine beans and taco mix. Spread in 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle green onions on top. Blend Miracle Whip and sour cream and spread over onions. Sprinkle olives and cheese on top. Chill and serve with Fritos.

title: mennonite slaw dressing
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, sugar, salt, celery seed and onion; mix well.
Stir in vinegar and milk.
Refrigerate and use as needed.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix ingredients together and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream rhubarb cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat again.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and sour cream.
Mix in rhubarb.
Put in greased 13 x 9 glass cake pan or Teflon coated.
Sprinkle on crumb topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: crisp chicken oven baked
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, egg white, milk to make batter, dip chicken breast halves into batter then coat with cornflake crumbs.
Bake in pre-heated 350° oven 1 hour in an uncovered baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion for 5 minutes and drain.
Add soup, sour cream and carrots.
Combine stuffing mix and butter or margarine. Put 1/2 stuffing mix on bottom of greased casserole, then squash mixture, then top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven until squash is tender.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender (about 10 minutes).
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Separate dough into triangles; place in an ungreased 10-inch pie plate (press seams).
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour filling into crust. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low setting for 6 hours (do not open lid while cooking).
Serve with rice and green peas.

title: crabmeat sandwich
directions: Combine cream cheese and onion in food processor until well blended.
Grate onion and mix with cheese.
Add egg yolk; mix well.
Add crabmeat.
Refrigerate 1 hour to stiffen and combine flavors.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place Holland rusks or toasted English muffins on baking sheet.
Place a slice of tomato on each. Top with crab mixture and grated cheese.
Bake 15 minutes. Serves 3 to 6.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake in jelly roll pan for 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: date and nut chews
directions: Place eggs in bowl; add salt and beat. Gradually beat in sugar and Karo; add dates and nuts. Mix well. Fold in flour. Pour into greased pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven; cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer ingredients, putting the rye bread on top in a pan. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: orange-cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together 2 times flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and sugar.
Add juice and rind of orange.
Add salad oil with enough boiling water to make 1 cup.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Bake 1 hour in a greased or sprayed loaf pan at 325°.
Store 24 hours before serving.
Serve with cream cheese.
Also can be toasted.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring well.
Gradually add milk, beating constantly with a wire whisk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper; remove from heat.
Coat 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Spread 1/4 cup white sauce in baking dish.
Top with half each of potatoes, onion and cheese sauce.
Repeat layers except for cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese and breadcrumbs.
Bake additional 5 minutes.

title: cinnamon lemon cookies(makes 6 dozen)
directions: To make cinnamon-sugar, stir together 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon.

title: lemon chicken with thyme
directions: In plastic bag, dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
In skillet in oil, brown chicken.
Take out chicken and brown onion. Add leftover flour.
Add broth, 3 tablespoons of lemon juice and thyme.
Return chicken and cook until chicken is cooked.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: bean dip with beef
directions: Brown hamburger with onions; drain.
Mix other ingredients in until heated.
Store in crock-pot or other dish you can heat up. Before serving, add shredded cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: carrot ring mold
directions: Mix and pour into well greased ring mold.
Bake 40 minutes in a pan of hot water at 300°.
Turn out on plate and fill center with peas, limas, etc. and decorate around mold with hot or pickled beets.

title: double surprise lemon pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar, flour and salt. Cream butter until soft and blend with sugar mixture. Add 3 well beaten eggs, reserving 1 teaspoon egg whites for topping. Grate lemon peel, then peel lemon, discarding the white membrane. Cut lemon in paper thin slices (should be 1/3 cup). Add lemon peel and slices and water to sugar mixture. Pour into pastry. Adjust top crust. Flute edges and cut vents. Brush with reserved egg white and sprinkle with sugar. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim off all visible fat. Cut steak lengthwise (with the grain) into thin strips (about 3/16-inch thick). Combine seasonings. Sprinkle over strips.
Mix well. Arrange strips of meat, flat and close together, on wire racks on a shallow cookie sheet.
Bake in a slow oven at 175° for 4 hours or until dry and almost crisp.
Cool on paper towels.
Store in airtight jars and keep in refrigerator.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Parboil vegetables. Mix soups; put a little of the soup mixture in the bottom of baking dish.
Alternate vegetables, soup and cheese.
Add a little celery salt.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Boil stew beef until tender. In bowl mix onion and mushroom soup together. Pour all into deep baking dish. Spoon in stew beef. Cook at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: raisin-maple zapples
directions: In a small bowl, mix raisins, syrup and spice to blend thoroughly. Core apples from stem ends with thin bladed knife or melon baller, leaving blossom ends intact. Peel top halves of apples.
Arrange apples, spaced apart, in a circle in shallow microwave-safe dish or pie plate.
Stuff apples with raisin mixture, dividing equally.
Pour orange juice over apples. Cover snugly with plastic wrap, venting one corner.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, turning a quarter turn after 5 minutes. Remove from microwave.
Loosen plastic wrap. Set aside 5 minutes. Serve warm with juice. Dollop with plain nonfat yogurt, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and beat until well blended and squash fibers do not collect on beaters.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sid's marinated carrots
directions: Mix well and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate in marinade 12 hours.
You can re-use marinade.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Prepare bacon (fry until crisp). Drain grease from beef and add all other ingredients including chipped bacon.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. This freezes well.

title: butterscotch fondue
directions: Heat butter, cream and brown sugar in fondue pot at high, stirring until melted and bubbly.
Mix cornstarch and rum together; pour into cream mixture, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium; continue cooking, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Set control at low for serving.

title: chocolate oat chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. For chewy cookies, bake 9 to 10 minutes.
And for crispy cookies, bake 12 to 13 minutes.
Let cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: golden sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and oleo together until well blended.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apricot salad
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup juice. Set aside. Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add marshmallows, stirring until melted. Stir in pineapple and apricot.
Chill until consistency of egg white. Combine cream cheese and pineapple juice, blending well.
Stir in whipped topping. Fold in gelatin. Arrange banana slices in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch greased dish. Spoon gelatin mixture over bananas. Sprinkle with pecans. Chill until firm.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with butter.
Set aside to cool.
Beat eggs. Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat in cooled chocolate and butter.
Add flour and salt.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while hot.

title: sausage and green chili strata
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Lightly butter one side of bread and cut into cubes.
Place half the bread into a buttered 8-inch baking dish; sprinkle with half the cheese and cover with the sausage and rest of cheese and bread.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings and pour over the casserole.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: mother's sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash potatoes and margarine.
Add other ingredients, coconut last.
Stir good.

Pour in buttered, deep 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake in a 375° preheated oven for 1 hour or more (ovens vary). It is done when it isn't soggy anymore and begins to turn dark and slightly crusty on top.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch oblong dish.
Mix pudding and milk together until thickens. Blend in ice cream.
Pour over cake and refrigerate 1 hour. Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix in strawberries and pour over cake.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Can frost with Cool Whip or leave plain.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients; spread evenly in shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the crumbs in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine egg whites, sugar, berries and lemon juice in a large bowl.
With electric beater, beat at high speed to stiff peaks, about 10 minutes. Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon over crumbs. Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight. Cut in 10 or 12 squares.
May trim with whole strawberries.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and 1/2 cup butter.
Add the Cheddar cheese, salt, pepper, onion, chicken soup and sour cream; mix well.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Top with cornflakes, mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop two pkgs. dried beef and mix with other ingredients. Form into ball. Cover ball with other pkg. of dried beef.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix everything together. Pour into uncooked pie shell (ready made is okay).
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Blend oleo and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugars.
Add oats, pecans, coconut, cornflakes and chips.
Drop by spoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet and mash flat.
They double in size.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
They burn easily.
Makes about 14 dozen.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Add mayo to desired consistency.
May 24 hours ahead of time. Keep refrigerated.

title: banana nut loaves (3)
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together dry ingredients and add, alternating with buttermilk.
Add bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Stir.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tests done.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add to beef.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In a large casserole, combine beans and brown sugar.
Stir in beef mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sour cream  pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar, beating until creamy.
Add egg yolks, beat well.
Add flour, salt, soda, beating to blend. Add sour cream, flavoring and mix well. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in tube pan or can make 3 to 4 layers.
Bake 315 degrees, 1 1/2 hours, for tube pan.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 4 to 5 hours on slow.
Do not stir often.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In a gumbo pot, mix oil and flour to make a roux (dark brown in color).
Add onions and celery and saute well.
Stir in green onions.
Add 1 gallon water and boil slowly for 1 hour.
Add parsley and shrimp; cook for 20 minutes on low fire.
Add crabmeat and oysters.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: grandma's syrup bread
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and egg; add milk and flour.
Melt oleo and shortening in baking pan (9 x 12-inch) and add this to batter. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: wadie sizers potato salad
directions: Season with salt and pepper.
Mix with slaw dressing and mayonnaise.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs through mixture and 1/2 cup on top.
Bake in a casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mamie's fudge
directions: In a medium saucepan, put sugar, salt, butter and milk, boil for 6 minutes.
In a large bowl, put chocolate chips, nut meats and marshmallow cream.
Pour boiling syrup over ingredients, beat until chocolate is melted and pour onto a cookie sheet that has been greased with margarine.
Let stand a few hours before cutting.
Store in a tin box.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until fluffy.
Add sugar slowly.
Beat slowly.
Add flavoring.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Roll into small balls about the size of marbles and press slightly.
Place apart on greased cookie sheet.
I use Pam.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for about 12 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta as directed; drain.
Meanwhile, cook and stir remaining ingredients, except parsley,
in medium saucepan until hot.
Pour sauce over hot pasta and toss to coat well.
Serve with parsley and extra Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix ricotta cheese with egg and 1/2 tsp. salt.
In large heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes, paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano. Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally about 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna as directed, drain.
In a 9 x 13 inch baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce.
Then alternate layers of lasagna, sauce, ricotta, mozzarella, and parmesan cheese, ending with sauce, mozzarella, and parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Allow to stand 15 minutes, cut into squares.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Beat eggs. Melt butter and put in baking dish.
Break apart into small pieces the bread.
Put into dish. Pour pineapple and syrup into dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no egg ice cream
directions: You will need a 4-quart freezer.

title: fashion show punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except sherbet; cool with ice cubes.
Put sherbet in punch while serving several scoops at a time.

title: almond cookies
directions: Spray a 9-inch square baking pan with olive oil cooking spray. Combine almonds, flour, sugars, cinnamon, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in egg and olive oil until blended. Transfer to prepared pan and, with floured fingers or spatula, press dough evenly into pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cut into diamonds.
Return pan to oven and bake 20 minutes more.
Cool before carefully removing cookies from pan. Yield:
20 small cookies.

title: corn salad relish
directions: Shred cabbage, onions and peppers.
Cut corn from cob and put all together in big pot.
Add sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar. Stir altogether and bring to a boil.
Boil for 20 minutes, stirring so as not to let it stick.
Pack into jars and seal.

title: vanilla ice cream-salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice until done.
Add other ingredients. Heat until bubbly and serve.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Peel banana; cut into pieces and put in a blender with milk and ice.
Put cover on blender and blend 15 to 20 seconds.
Pour into glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar very well.
Add vanilla. Slowly add sifted flour and blend well.
Put through cookie press using star plate to form wreaths.
Decorate with red and green candied cherries and sprinkles.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
I usually do 4 times the amount.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion, peppers and tomatoes in butter.
Stir in paprika and flour.
Add cheese.
Heat slowly for about 10 minutes, until cheese melts.
(Do not stir until cheese melts.)
Serve as a warm dip with corn chips or dribble over baked enchiladas or tacos. (Dip becomes thick when cool.
Reheat with a tablespoon of water. Dip may be frozen.)

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Blend first six ingredients.
Stir in chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cake can be plain or iced.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Grate cheese. Mix with other ingredients.
Roll into balls and bake at 350°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crabmeat pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta in water according to package directions (omitting salt).
Drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except crabmeat.
Then stir in crabmeat.
Chill before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In order, put all ingredients into a 2-quart oblong casserole and beat with a fork.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10. Delicious, easy and perfect for company brunch served with ham and a fruit salad.
Freezes well.

title: caramel pie
directions: In a bowl mix 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar, dash of salt, 1/2 tsp vanila, 1/3 cup milk, 4 egg yolks, (save whites for later). Stir well!
Add 1 1/6 cup milk & stir in.
Carmelize 1 1/2 cup sugar in an iron skillet stirring constantly on low heat - when sugar melts, stir in butter ( about the size of an egg).
After butter is stirrred in add bowl mixture a tiny bit at a time while continuing to stir.
Stir rapidly until thickened and pour into crust.
Add meringue.

title: honey bear brownies(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Blend in honey and vanilla. Add eggs. Combine flour, cocoa and salt. Add dry mixture to creamed mixture. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool before cutting or frosting.

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Mix ground round, eggs, bread crumbs, milk, ketchup and seasonings as meat loaf.
Flatten and arrange on a sheet of tinfoil.
Top with thawed, drained broccoli. Top with ham.
Roll, using foil to start.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 1/4 hours at 350°. Top with cheese.
Melt 1 minute.

title: sticky pull-apart buns
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Mix together dough balls with brown sugar, pudding and nuts.
Let dough rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; sift flour, soda and cinnamon together.
Add alternating with milk and sherry.
Add nuts and fruits and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken royal palm
directions: Wrap each chicken breast half around heart of palm.
Spread each with butter.
Bake at 350° for
40 minutes.
Serve Hollandaise Sauce over top.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt butter and shortening; let it cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Hand stir together.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Makes approximately 2 dozen cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in coffee and applesauce.
Measure flour by sifting.
Mix remaining ingredients; stir into applesauce mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: cream cheese kolacky
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on floured board to about 1/8-inch thick; cut into small squares. Fill each with 1/4 teaspoon filling or preserves.
Overlap opposite corners and press together.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Done when bottom is light brown.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Combine bulgur wheat and water in medium bowl; cover and let stand 1 hour or until water is absorbed.
Drain bulgur.
Press excess water from wheat using fork.
Press lettuce and parsley between paper towels to dry.
Toss together in large bowl.
Add bulgur, tomatoes, onion, mint and garlic; toss gently.
Combine lemon juice, olive oil, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Stir with whisk; pour dressing over salad.
Chill 1 hour.

title: italian biscuits (biscotti)
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually add the flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add anise seed last; mix well.
Spoon on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until light tan.
Slice and put back in oven to toast them.
This is a Christmas recipe.

title: oil pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt; add oil, stirring until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle with water (1 tablespoon at a time), stirring quickly.
Gather into ball.
Roll dough into 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Place in 9-inch pie plate.
Makes 1 pie crust.

title: better than sex cake(9 x 13-inch cake pan)
directions: Cover cake with bananas.
Mix cream cheese, pudding and milk. Cover bananas with this mixture.
Cover pudding mixture with 12 ounces of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut, chopped pecans and chopped cherries.
Keep cake chilled.

title: pastry(no fail!)
directions: Makes two crusts plus
lattice
tops
of one crust plus full top crust.

title: torte de banana (brazilian banana tart)
directions: Peel bananas and press through sieve.
Put pulp into saucepan with sugar, salt and butter.
Stir and cook until mixture starts to boil.
Remove from fire and cool.
(If firmer mixture is desired, 1 teaspoon gelatin may be added at this point.)
When it is cool, whip in the wine or lime juice and nutmeg.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: dragon king's chicken
directions: Rinse chicken, drain and dry well.
Combine soy sauce, sherry and ginger.
Pour over chicken in large plastic bag.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Combine tea and brown sugar; sprinkle evenly over foil lined pan.
Place chicken breast side up on rack over tea mixture.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Discard foil.
Increase to 400°.
Bake 30 minutes or until tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before carving.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drip milk over the top to brown.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Mix together all ingredients with 1 cup of water.
Cook 2 to 3 hours in crock-pot.

title: easy butter cake with lemon filling
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Beat together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Beat on low until mixed well. Beat on high about 3 minutes, scraping sides of bowl.
Pour batter into pans. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing.
Split layers in 1/2.
Spread Lemon Filling between layers.
Top with Butter Frosting.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry the onions and celery in the margarine until brown (use large frypan). Add flour and seasoning; slowly add the water. Stir constantly until thickened. Cook 15 minutes. Add tomatoes, peas, vinegar, sugar and shrimp. Continue cooking 10 minutes more until shrimp is thoroughly heated. Spoon rice on individual plates and spoon shrimp sauce over the top. Yields 6 servings.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well. Use one heaping teaspoonful per cup.

title: top of stove pot roast
directions: Dredge roast with flour on all sides.
Heat a heavy pan or Dutch oven over moderate heat.
Brown roast slowly, using no fat. When brown, place a rack under meat.
Add water and white vinegar. Cover and simmer over very low heat until tender.
Half an hour before serving, add salt, pepper and mustard.
Blend into juices, adding more liquid if desired.

title: american strudel
directions: Blend together margarine and sour cream.
Mix in flour to make a soft ball of dough.
Refrigerate one hour.
Divide into 3 balls. Mix apples and raisins.
Roll pastry into very thin rectangles. Fill one end with filling and roll up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put all three rolls on sheet spaced apart.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
When cooked, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hot lightning
directions: Put potatoes (cut side down), bacon or sausage and butter in a casserole.
Add salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add the apples or pears and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer or until potatoes and fruit are tender.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix together ingredients and roll into small balls.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Cook onions, peppers, mushrooms and garlic until tender. Stir in rest of ingredients.
Cook until fish flakes.
Serve over rice.
Add a hot sauce (optional).

title: mixed pickles
directions: In large nonmetal container, cover first 3 ingredients with a mixture of 3/4 cup salt and 6 cups of water. Cover and let stand in cool place overnight.
Drain.
Rinse.
Place in large kettle.

title: pink party punch
directions: Pour in all juices first.
Mix.
Add sherbet and pour over ice cubes.
Add soda last.
Serves 20.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Mix with browned beef.
Stuff in green peppers.
Cook in oven until rice is tender at 325°.

title: mock honey
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil; cook about 5 minutes.
Pour into jar and store in refrigerator.
Makes good ice cream topping or as honey on toast or biscuits.

title: aztec calender
directions: Assemble in the following 5 layers on a large round plate: Mix beans, taco seasoning and picante sauce. Spread on plate for first layer. Mash avocados with sour cream, lemon juice and garlic salt. Spread over bean mixture on plate. Add green chili and onions. Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Decorate with olives, tomatoes and parsley. Sprinkle with chili powder. Add fresh parsley. Can be made a day ahead of time. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken sorrentino(for 2)
directions: Dip chicken cutlets in flour, then beaten eggs.
Fry on medium heat in hot oil until golden brown; set aside.
Dip eggplant in flour, then eggs and fry in same oil, until golden brown.
Set aside.
Put Marsala wine, butter, salt, pepper and chicken broth into clean frying pan.
Saute chicken cutlets for about 10 minutes in mixture over low heat.
Add slices of eggplant over chicken. Top with thin slices of Mozzarella.
Cover; simmer for 3 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Put frozen bread in a baking pan and set in cool oven over night. In the morning take bread out of oven. Preheat oven to 350 degrees, With a knife poke holes all over the bread to deflate a little. Mix together sugar and whipping cream, pour over bread. Make sure mixture gets in all holes. Bake 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake vigorously.
Pour marinade over shrimp; cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Saute in marinade until shrimp turn white, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve shrimp over cooked rice pilaf.
Makes 3 servings.

title: cinnamon pickle rings
directions: Peel and sliced cucumbers 1/3 to 1/2 inch thick.
Remove seeds (leaving round hole; I use an apple core knife).
Makes 2 gallons. Soak 24 hours in lime and 8 1/2 quarts water.
Drain and wash. Soak in cool water for 3 hours.
Drain well!

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour and melted butter with a beater.
Pour on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake following directions on cake mix box.
Remove baked cake and poke holes through cake and pour the can of condensed milk over cake.
Let cake cool, the pour jar of caramel topping over cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Crush and sprinkle Butterfinger candy bars on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate cake. Best if cake is refrigerated overnight before served.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix zucchini, shortening and egg.
Add soda, flour, spices and salt, then raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about three dozen.

title: macaroni toss
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Cook peas as directed on package; drain (canned peas may be used).
Mix macaroni, peas, cheese, relish, mayonnaise and chopped onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with a fork to flatten.
Bake in 325° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad(low calorie)
directions: Use juice from fruit to dissolve Jell-O. Mix all ingredients together. Do not try substitutes. Contains natural enzymes to increase metabolism and helps burn calories. Keeps fresh in refrigerator for 2 weeks. Good to eat anytime.

title: blue ribbon cookies
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Mix last three ingredients together. Then gradually add them together.
Cover and chill for one hour.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 400° for about 6 to 8 minutes, or until edges are just turning golden.
Top with decorations or icing after baking.

title: icebox cukes(pickles)
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions in thin slices. Mix all other ingredients together and pour over slices. Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 2 days, stirring once a day. Put into jars and keep refrigerated.

title: turkey roulade
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together cranberry sauce and barbecue sauce.
Brush one side of each turkey breast with some of the sauce mixture.
Place several green pepper strips crosswise on the sauced side of each turkey breast.
Roll up jell-roll style from short side; secure bundles with wooden toothpicks.
Place turkey bundles, seam side down, in an ungreased 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions. Saute onion and celery in margarine. Combine all ingredients together in large bowl. Pour into buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix until stiff.
Roll out into thin layer.
Slice into 3-inch strips.
Stack strips on top of each other (using flour between). Slice with sharp knife to desired width.
Dry.
Cook in boiling water (lightly salted) 5 minutes.

title: white trash
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients all together.
Melt white chocolate in microwave (1/2 to 2 minutes).
Mix peanut butter with chocolate. Put first mixture on wax paper and pour white
chocolate mixture over.
Coat well.
When dry, break all into pieces.

title: seafood stuffed eggplant
directions: Boil shrimp.
Peel,
devein
and
chop
then set aside. Cut each eggplant into lengthwise and remove middle.
Chop and add to skillet with onion, celery, garlic and butter.
Simmer, covered, until done.
Tear
bread
and
soak
with
eggs until completely saturated.
Mix
with
shrimp,
eggplant
mixture, parsley, onion tops
and
crabmeat.
Season to your own taste. Cover eggplant shells with
water and boil 10 minutes or until tender.
Stuff with shrimp
mixture and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling over an 8 x 12-inch pan. Spread pineapple over pie filling, then add sugar, cake mix (dry), then melted margarine. Spread pecans evenly over top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chuck roast with mushroom sauce
directions: Sear roast beef in fat until brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Add cream of mushroom soup and dried onion soup to top of roast.
Cook until tender at 325°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries and juice.
Pour in greased Bundt or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set. Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on top of set Jell-O.
Top with pretzels, butter and sugar that have been mixed together.

title: breaded hamburger
directions: Make hamburger into patties and put into cracker crumbs.
Dip into the beaten eggs and pat in cracker crumbs again.
Fry in oil until crisp.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and rinse pasta.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and garlic and mix into rinsed pasta.
Add sliced onion and cucumbers; mix well. Chill and serve.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Soften cheese and chop olives and nuts.
Mix together.
Makes about 2 pints.
Refrigerate 48 hours before using.

title: coke cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together flour and sugar.
Set aside and boil the butter, Coke and cocoa.
Pour over the flour and sugar and mix well.
Add to the mixture buttermilk, eggs, salt, vanilla and soda; blend well.
Add marshmallows.
Mixture will be thin and marshmallows will float.
Bake in
a greased, floured pan for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma struck's applesauce cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in applesauce.
Cream sugar, margarine and eggs together.
Add applesauce mixture and flour mixture alternately to the creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins last.
Oil and flour an angel food pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: simple lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add salt and garlic salt or powder.
Add tomato sauce.
Let this mixture simmer while cooking the lasagna noodles according to package instructions.

title: butternut squash
directions: Halve squash; remove seed.
Peel and cut into chunks.
Cook in salted boiling water until tender (20 minutes).
Drain and mash. Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
For variety, try 1/4 teaspoon ginger.

title: trash bag candy
directions: Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in saucepan over low heat until all melted.
Gently fold in Rice Chex until all are covered.
Dump into a large bowl and pour box of sugar and shake well until all covered.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together. Add dry mixture alternately with milk to the egg mixture, blending well after each addition.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from pans at once and roll in melted butter, then in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Cool on rack.
Makes 12.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Mix butter with Ricotta until creamy.
Add sugar gradually until well blended.
Add eggs to mixture.
Beat until creamy. Slowly add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes. Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.
Makes a lot of cookies.
Great of holidays.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses, beating well.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to preceding mixture. Mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll in 1-inch balls, then roll in sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at approximately 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: endless cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, peppers and onion in a large bowl.
In a one quart saucepan, combine vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour hot dressing over cabbage mixture and toss well.
Stand at room temperature 30 to 60 minutes, tossing occasionally.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 2 days before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in a skillet.
Add next 2 ingredients.
In a saucepan, mix next 4 ingredients.

title: chicken livers with rice
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in pan; add onion and cook until tender.
Add to rice and cook as package directs.
Meanwhile, roll livers in seasoned flour.
Saute in remaining butter until brown. Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole with livers, rice, soup and rest of the ingredients.
Bake until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes at 375°.
Plain or yellow rice may be used.
Cook first and then measure right amount and mix with other ingredients.

title: popular cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and dried beef together.
Add a dash of Accent and Worcestershire sauce (to suit your own taste).
Add as much green onions as liked.
Form into ball and chill.
Set out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: key lime pie
directions: Stir together limeade and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in freezer for 1 hour.
Set out 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with lime slices or strawberries.

title: potato salad
directions: Toss potatoes, eggs, bacon and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Toss with potato mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Makes 60 to 70 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Place vegetables, beans, macaroni, celery and onions in a bowl and refrigerate.
Mix sugar, flour, vinegar and water in a small saucepan.
Heat and stir continuously until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool and pour over vegetable mixture and mix well. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients into ungreased 9-inch square baking pan. Makes 3 depressions.
Distribute the oil among the depressions, then the vinegar and vanilla.
Pour the cold water over all.

title: simply chocolate mousse
directions: Cook over medium heat just until boiling, stirring constantly. Cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Fold in 1/2 cup whipping cream.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Chill several hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain the Mexicorn. Add chopped bell pepper, chopped onion, chopped tomato, small jar drained pimentos, few tablespoons mayonnaise, dash of salt and plenty of pepper.
Great for picnics or anytime you want something quick.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread into a 8 1/2	x 4 1/2
x 2 1/2 inch loaf pan. Bake 1 hour.
Drain excess drippings.
Spoon chili sauce over cooked meat loaf; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake an additional 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: mu's no fail chess pie
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Cool until firm.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Continue beating while dropping in spoonfuls of sugar mixture.
Add vanilla (very stiff batter).
Bake in unbaked shell for 1 hour.

title: bees nest cake
directions: For low-fat and lower calorie, use sugar-free pudding, skim milk and light yellow cake mix.

title: brownies
directions: Melt together in saucepan butter and chocolate squares.
After melted, remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into an 8-inch pan that has been greased with butter.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes in 375° oven.

title: pecan bread
directions: Add ingredients in order as given.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together in a glass jar and let stand in refrigerator over night.

title: pineapple cheese salad ring
directions: Rub cottage cheese through a sieve.
Add salt.
Soak gelatin in cold water and dissolve over hot water.
Add cheese, mix well.
Add mayonnaise, pineapple and cream.
Chill in ring until firm.
When ready, unmold and serve with a dressing of mayonnaise, plus a little lemon juice and a little whipped cream.
Use fresh fruit in center of ring.

title: dorothea's salsa
directions: Cook everything together except the tomato paste.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Then add tomato paste (if you do not have paste, use tomato sauce or tomato puree).
Bring to boil.
You can put this salsa in jars and seal them.

title: hot mushroom dip(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Slice mushrooms and onion.
Saute in 4 tablespoons butter until lightly browned.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and flour.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese and parsley on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve hot with crackers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add half the flour blend.
Add all the chopped apples; blend.
Add remaining flour and beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: better than ever cake
directions: Prepare cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.
Cook sugar and pineapple together until sugar has dissolved.
Spread on cake.

title: brunswick stew
directions: When you stop cooking, add tomato ketchup and salt and sugar to taste. This will make 30 gallons.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Mix with spoon.
Batter will be thick.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and frost with 4x sugar (optional).

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients until mixed well. Serve with your favorite raw vegetables.

title: cheese ball
directions: Place cheeses in small mixer bowl, let stand at room temperature until softened.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce, blend at low speed.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy, scraping side and bottom of bowl.
Cover, chill at least 8 hours.
Shape mixture into one large ball or small balls.
Roll in pecans.
Place on serving plate.
Cover and chill two hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soup and pepper and pour over the beans that have been drained.
Add 1/2 can of onions and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli; mix broccoli, raisins, and oranges and set aside. In another bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar, and sugar; gently fold into the broccoli mixture. Add cashews and bacon crumbles.

title: chicken 'n coke
directions: Roll chicken in flour, salt and pepper. Place in skillet and just barely brown.
Pour coke and barbecue sauce over chicken. Cover with lid and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place 6 or 8 pork chops in sauce and cook until tender.
Salt to taste.

title: hamburger or chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except fried onion rings and cheese together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Top with cheese, then fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (depends on hot fast the hash browns thaw).

title: best ever biscuits
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together. Turn out onto floured board. Knead and roll out. Cut with biscuit cutter and place on lightly greased or nonstick baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and set for 3 hours.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together and spread over cool crust. Mix pudding and milk together; spread over cream cheese layer. Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with toasted coconut.

title: chicken breasts ala bolognese
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half and pound lightly.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and parsley.
Dredge chicken into seasoned flour. Heat olive oil and butter.
Add chicken; saute quickly to a golden brown.
Lightly sprinkle with garlic salt.
Remove from heat and layer with Prosciutto and cheese slices.
Sprinkle grated cheese and pour chicken stock into skillet.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes, until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put in saucepan and stir until cheese melts:
onion, cream cheese, Cheddar cheese (cut in pieces) and 2 cans soup.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Mix together broccoli, rice and sauce. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in oven preheated to 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Combine the 2 mixtures and mix well until smooth.
Add 1 cup of nuts.
Pour into three 1-pound greased coffee cans (fill cans halfway).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Quarter the biscuits with kitchen shears. Dip shears in water after each cut to keep the biscuits from getting too sticky. Dip biscuits into sugar mixture and place in a greased tube pan. Do this until all biscuits are used. Melt butter or margarine and mix in 3/4 cup sugar. Pour mixture over biscuits. Bake in a preheated 350°F (175°C) oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, almonds, olives and 1/2 of cheese. Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix all these together.
Pour into greased casserole.
Mix chips and remaining cheese; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine
sugar,
corn	syrup,	water
and
salt.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Cook slowly without
stirring,	to 265° (or when small amount dropped into cold water	forms very hard ball).	Beat the egg whites stiff. Gradually
pour
hot syrup into egg whites, beating constantly until
mixture
holds
shape.
Add	vanilla.
Spoon
it out on waxed paper.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: rosettes
directions: Dip rosette iron in batter and fry in oil.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or three 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Pour into pans. Bake about 70 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: vegetable cheese bake
directions: In a saucepan combine frozen vegetables and boiling water. Bring to a boil again.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain well. Melt the margarine in a saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Cook for 1 minute; gradually stir in milk.
Simmer, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Mix in vegetables and onions.
Spread into buttered 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: strawberry-banana daiquiri
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix until ice is smooth. Garnish with fresh strawberry, lime and whipped cream.
Serves 4.

title: garbage cake
directions: Mix all together in bowl.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix together.
Roll thin, about 1/8-inch thick.
Layer on waxed paper, putting waxed paper between each layer.
Bake at 75° to 100° with layers stacked.
Remove top layer when dry.
Continue baking and removing top layer until all layers are done.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: After mixing ingredients thoroughly, bake 1 hour at 300° in unbaked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: candy yams(lynelle's special)
directions: Slice yams and lay in baking pan.
Add vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and evaporated milk.
Bake for 15 minutes at about 300°. Add marshmallows and continue to bake for 5 minutes.
This is usually served hot.

title: granddad's pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar and pumpkin. Mix well. Sift together dry ingredients. Blend with pumpkin mixture. Add flavoring and nuts. Pout into 3 well greased loaf pans or 4 coffee cans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Delicious!

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix salmon, margarine and eggs.
Stir in crumbs.
Mix soda and buttermilk; stir in until blended.
Cook in loaf pan about 30 minutes.

title: western pound cake
directions: *Sift the flour 3 times, then measure sugar box full of flour.

title: halloween grease paint
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients on white plate with rubber spatula, forming a smooth paste.
Add 3 to 4 drops glycerin for a creamy consistency, then add food coloring, a drop at a time. Using fingers and stroking in 1 directions, spread mixture over face.

title: broccoli-walnut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Put in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In pan, melt 1/2 cup butter. Blend in flour and cubes; stir to make smooth paste.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Pour sauce over broccoli.
Mix in a bit.
Heat 2/3 cup water and 6 tablespoons butter until melted.
Pour over stuffing mix and toss to coat.
Add nuts and put on top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream and dill chicken
directions: Place chicken in single layers in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with pepper.
Combine soup mix, sour cream, lemon juice, dill and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Serve over noodles.

title: garlic grits casserole
directions: Cook grits and water together for 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Melt cheese and margarine; add to grits.
Beat eggs and milk together; add salt and put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup crushed buttered corn flakes on top and bake for 4 to 5 minutes, until knife blade comes out clean.

title: chicken sauce piquante
directions: Fry pieces of chicken in oil until brown.
Remove chicken from pot.
Add onions, bell pepper, garlic and celery to oil and cook until transparent.
Add other ingredients.
Add water.
Add seasonings (red pepper makes it piquante).
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Will take from 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake by directions.
Add sugar to taste.
Punch holes in cool cake; pour coconut milk in holes in cake.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Prepare cake following directions on box.
Bake in sheet form. Let cool.

title: one-pan potatoes and pepper steak
directions: While potatoes cook, toss beef with garlic pepper and heat oil in large skillet over high heat. Add beef and toss 3 minutes. Remove beef. Add green pepper to skillet; toss 3 minutes. Add potatoes; saute 5 minutes. Add beef; toss until heated through. Season with salt.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add beans.
Simmer 15 minutes. Mix salad with lettuce, cheese, onion and tomatoes.
Mix together dressing and chips with salad mixture.
Add meat and beans to salad mixture and toss.

title: chocolate sour cream frosting
directions: In a saucepan, melt chocolate pieces and butter or margarine over low heat, stirring frequently.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream, vanilla and salt.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating by hand until frosting is smooth.
Spread frosting over cooled cake.
Frosts tops of two 8 or 9-inch layers, top of one 13 x 9-inch or about 18 cupcakes.

title: spiced pickled beets
directions: I just buy 2 cans of small beets at the store, drain.

title: far east celery
directions: Cook celery in boiling water about 8 minutes until crisp. Drain.
Mix celery with chestnuts, soup and pimento.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs, almonds and melted margarine together; spread over celery.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6 people.

title: ann's breakfast quiche
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie pan. Place ham, cheese and eggs in bottom of pan. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie pan. Bake until golden brown, 30 to 35 minutes at 400°. Let stand about 5 minutes before serving.

title: slush
directions: Combine in blender.
Pour into ice cube trays and freeze.
To serve, put cubes in bowl and pour ginger ale or 7-Up over.

title: chicken and dressing(microwave)
directions: Bone and skin chicken breasts.
Mix dressing with water. Place a serving mound of dressing in dish for each piece of chicken.
Place a piece of chicken on top of dressing.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and microwave on High 4 minutes for 1 piece, 6 minutes for 2 pieces, 8 minutes for 3 pieces, 10 minutes for 4 pieces, 14 to 15 minutes for 6 pieces and 17 to 20 minutes for 8 pieces.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Beat soft butter/margarine, granulated sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water until creamy. Beat in eggs. Sift flour, baking soda and salt and add.

Add ground nuts. Spread in two 13 x 9-inch pans which have been greased. Sprinkle each pan with chocolate chips. Bake at 375° for 2 minutes. Run knife through dough to marbleize. Bake 15 minutes more. Cool and cut into squares.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer ingredients in pan in order given.
Do not mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In a large bowl, combine the milk and 2 pkgs. instant vanilla pudding.
Add the cream cheese mixture to the pudding mixture along with the Cool Whip.
Place the Cool Whip lid in the bottom of your 8 inch plastic pot, then alternate layers of "dirt" (crushed Oreos), and pudding mixture, ending with dirt. Top off with a plastic flower arrangement.
Keep your Dirt Cake cool and serve with a trowel.

title: caramel corn in microwave
directions: Bring to a boil on full power the oleo, salt, brown sugar and Karo, 2 or 3 minutes, then boil exactly 3 minutes.
Remove.
Stir in soda and pour over popcorn.
Add peanuts, if you want to. Return to microwave for 3 minutes on High, stirring every 30 seconds.
Pour out to cool.

title: oatmeal-coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Drain artichokes and chop.
Mix all ingredients together. Spoon into lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with assorted crackers.

title: sonora chicken tacos
directions: In a bowl combine diced chicken and salsa.
Top with shredded Cheddar and microwave until cheese is melted and chicken and salsa are warmed through.
Stir until evenly mixed.
Serve in warm flour tortillas.
Serves approximately 4.

title: pork sausage
directions: Peel the apples and cut in thin slices or 8ths.
Spread out on a clean white cloth and place in sun a few days.
Be sure to cover with a screen or very thin cloth to keep out flies.
They can be dried in a hot attic, a sunny window or in the oven, very low. The slices will darken and get wrinkled when completely dry. Store in cloth bags.

title: spiced banana pudding
directions: Add
spice
to milk.
Mix pudding and milk according to directions	on pudding box.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix
in 6 cup bowl.
Cool in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours before serving.
May
top
with Cool Whip if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sad day cake
directions: Mix all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: gourmet meat dish
directions: Use a large, heavy skillet.
Season meat.
Get skillet very hot.
Sear meat on both sides.
Turn down heat to medium-low. Slice onion and lay on top of meat.
Add garlic, mushrooms and all other ingredients.
Cover skillet and cook over medium-low heat until meat is tender.
You will love this!
(Option:
You can add 2 to 3 tablespoons cooking wine.)

title: quick veggie chili
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and other vegetables in a large pot. Add the chili beans, tomatoes and potatoes.
(If you have whole tomatoes, cut them up.
If you have fresh tomatoes, remove skin, then add to the pot.
Using fresh tomatoes tastes great, but chili must simmer longer.)
Add bouillon and spices. Simmer until potatoes are done.
Serve with grated Cheddar cheese and sour cream on top.

title: rose's chocolate cake(large 3 layer cake)
directions: Mix cocoa and boiling water.
Let cool.
Combine dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Alternate chocolate mixture and dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) round pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.
Use favorite frosting.
Makes nice large cake.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with salted water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook about 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes and cool slightly.
Stir in butter and pepper; toss lightly.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and peanut butter.
Add melted margarine and mix quickly and well with hands.
Pat into greased 13 x 9-inch pan, lined with foil and greased.
Spread evenly with hands.
Let cool.
Cut no bigger than bite-size pieces, because candy is rich.

title: quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees.

title: potato cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flavoring.
Add egg; mix well. Add potato flakes and Bisquick.
Mix well; put in refrigerator and chill.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: megan's morning munchies(method:  stick)
directions: Place one marshmallow in the hole of each donut.
Push end of toasting stick through side of donut, into marshmallow and through other side of donut.
Hold over hot coals until marshmallow is melted.
Use care when removing from toasting stick; melted sugar is very hot.

title: iron skillet kielbasa
directions: In iron skillet brown potatoes in a little oil.
Add kielbasa, onion, parsley, garlic and Italian seasoning.
Add green beans.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except 3 wieners in blender and mix. Cut the wieners into thin slices and put into other mixture.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Filling:
Cook pudding mix according to directions on package, using the 1 1/2 cups milk.
Remove from heat.
Cover with plastic wrap to help keep a skin from forming.
Refrigerate until cool, then stir in bananas.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar, melted butter, syrup, salt and vanilla. Spread pecans in pie shell. Pour in egg mixture and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until filling is firm. Nuts will rise to the top of pie and form a crusty layer.

title: mississippi lemon chess pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine the sugar, flour and corn meal by tossing lightly with a fork.
Add the eggs, lemon juice and rind. Add milk and melted butter.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 375° or until top is golden brown and center is firm.
Delicious served warm.

title: banana bread(makes 3 loaves)
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine spices, baking soda, salt and flour.
Add to above mixture.
Add vanilla, bananas and nuts; mix well.
Flour and grease 3 loaf pans (1 pound).
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix last 5 ingredients together.
Pour over bean mixture and marinate a few hours or overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses to room temperature and combine.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce, half of the pecans and half the parsley. Form into a ball and roll in remaining nuts and parsley.
Chill until firm.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix together everything except butter and vanilla.
Let come to a full boil.
Boil 4 minutes.
Let stand without stirring for 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat and pour into buttered dish.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Save for use in soups or sauces. Brush mushroom caps with oil and place in buttered baking dish. In a mixing bowl, combine crabmeat, egg, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and 1/2 of the bread crumbs.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Combine remaining bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle over crab mixture.
Bake in preheated oven (375°) for 15 minutes. I usually double recipe.

title: pork chili
directions: Saute bacon
until
crisp.
Drain
all but 1 tablespoon fat. Stir in onions and pork.
Saute for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add
salt,
pepper,
chili
powder, bell peppers, tomatoes, tomato
sauce and reserved bean liquid. Also add bay leaf, oregano, Worcestershire sauce and tomato juice.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2
to
2 hours until tender.
Stir in beans and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Skim fat.

title: hamburger paprikash with noodles and broccoli
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat, breaking up any large chunks.
Stir in garlic and frozen onion and pepper. Cook until thawed.
Stir in paprika and thyme.
Add broth, noodles and broccoli and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring twice, until noodles are tender.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender; drain.
Meanwhile, cook onion in 3 tablespoons butter until just soft.
Stir in soup (undiluted), salt, pepper, cheese and cooked carrots.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Toss bread stuffing mix with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Spoon over carrots.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through, about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crispy yeast waffles
directions: In large mixer bowl combine flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
In saucepan, heat milk, water and butter until very warm (120° to 130°; butter does not need to melt).
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and foil; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Stir down batter.
Bake on waffle iron on medium heat.
Serve hot with butter and toppings.
Yields 6 to 8 waffles.
(Can keep for a week in refrigerator.)

title: sunday casserole
directions: Vegetables may be
sliced
and
chopped a day ahead and placed in plastic bag and refrigerated.
Cut steak in serving size pieces;
season
with
salt
and pepper.
Place in large casserole dish,
sprayed
with
Pam.
Add vegetables and pour soup
and water over all.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in very slow oven, 2 1/2 to 3 hours while you go to church.

title: seven minute icing(this recipe tries to beat the clock.)
directions: In a double boiler, combine all ingredients.
While cooking, beat with hand whip or electric mixer for seven minutes.
Remove from heat and spread on cake.

title: danish-style new potatoes
directions: In a medium size heavy saucepan, bring 3 cups unsalted water to a boil. Add the potatoes and simmer, partially covered, for 15 minutes or until the potatoes are tender. Drain and cool for 10 minutes; peel off the skins and set aside. Put the 1/4 cup water and the brown sugar into a 10-inch skillet over moderate heat; bring to a simmer and cook, stirring until the sugar has dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add the margarine and continue to cook, stirring until it has melted, about 1 minute. Add the potatoes and toss until heated through, about 2 minutes longer. Sprinkle with the dill. Serves 4.

title: ice cream lemon pie
directions: Combine ice cream and lemonade in blender until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until firm (1 1/2 hours).
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with lemon twists.

title: chicken brunch bake
directions: In a large bowl, toss bread crumbs and broth. Add chicken, rice, pimentos, parsley and salt. Mix well. Transfer to greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour eggs over mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Makes 8 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain grease.
In saucepan, add sauce, hamburger meat and noodles.
Fill empty jar of sauce mix with water and stir in meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Cover with cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: cheesy vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables and place in 13 X 9 pan. Sprinkle with lemon-pepper seasoning. In medium bowl, melt velveeta and margarine until smooth. Stir in miracle whip, lemon juice and milk. Beat until smooth and creamy. Pour over vegetables. Crush ritz crackers and top casserole. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes, until bubbly.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Blend together sugar, vinegar and salt.
Then pour this over vegetables.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in dry cake mix, cherry pie filling and oil and blend.
Spread in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
(Surface of cake will appear bumpy.)
Cool completely.

title: cherry sauce
directions: Mix juice and cornstarch.
Pour cherry pie filling and juice in pan and heat until thickened.
This is good on top of ham.

title: pickles
directions: Pack small, washed cucumbers into sterile jars.
Start with a grape leaf in bottom and 1 clove garlic (optional).
Boil together the vinegar, water, canning salt and sugar; pour over cucumbers. Add dill.
Seal and process for 10 minutes.
Really good dills.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together and set aside. Peel and quarter apples. Wrap crescent roll around apple, starting with wide end.

Place in a 9 x 14-inch pan. Pour melted butter over dumplings, then sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over dumplings. Pour Mountain Dew between dumplings. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes 16 dumplings.

title: davis pastry(pie crust)
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut into shortening.
Sprinkle in enough water to make a moist dough.
Roll out 1/2 of dough at a time.
This recipe will make a large 2-crust pie.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat
buttermilk
to
lukewarm.
Stir
in
cooking oil, sugar, soda and
salt.
Dissolve
yeast in warm water.
Add to buttermilk mixture, with unbeaten egg, stirring to blend.
Mix in flour all at	once.
Turn
out
on floured board and knead lightly
for several minutes to form a smooth ball.
Cover and let stand 5 or 10 minutes to tighten dough.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix bread crumbs, milk, margarine, sugar, eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg and raisins.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° with pan of water beneath for 45 minutes, or until knife comes out clean. Serve warm with lemon or chocolate sauce.

title: miracle pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into 10-inch greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
A crust will form on the bottom, pie filling is the center and a coconut topping above.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and alternate with banana.
Blend well after each addition.
Add walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow frosting
directions: Cook sugar and milk to a soft ball stage.
Add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and butter.
Stir until melted and thoroughly blended.
Cool and spread on cake.

title: creme brulee
directions: Preheat oven to 300 and line the bottom of a large baking pan with a damp kitchen cloth.
Bring a large pot of water to boil.

title: pie in the sky
directions: Bake ready-mixed pie shell according to directions.
Beat egg whites until mixed; add salt and vinegar; beat until stiff. Spread over bottom of baked pie shell and up the sides.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: salmon ball(a canape spread for crackers)
directions: Break up salmon pieces and mix in cream cheese and onion.
Add liquid smoke.
Mix well so that not large pieces of salmon remain. Form into a ball and roll in chopped walnuts to cover.
Serve as a spread for crackers.
Ritz are especially good with salmon spread.

title: chicken delicious casserole
directions: Place chicken in greased 3-quart casserole.
Cover with soup to which celery and mayo have been added.
Sprinkle with chestnuts.
Mix stuffing with butter and cover casserole with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Use a big bowl.
Preheat oven to slow 250°.
Grease and flour 9 x 3-inch tube pan.
Combine cherries and other fruits; toss with flour to coat.
Add nuts and coconut; toss.
Add sweetened milk and mix well.
Spoon into pan and smooth evenly.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan on rack.
Remove from pan and wrap tightly in foil.
Refrigerate for 2 weeks.
Good Christmas cake.
Serves 32 thin slices.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered dish and bake at 400° for one hour.

title: angel squares
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add whole egg and egg yolk.
Beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Spread mixture about 1/2-inch thick in greased baking pan.
Beat egg white.
Add brown sugar and beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla and spread this over the first mixture.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
(If you use self-rising flour, leave out salt and baking powder.)

title: turkey lasagna
directions: 1. Brown turkey in a large skillet, drain off fat. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, sweet basil, garlic
salt, and pepper.
2. Bring to a vigorous simmer while stirring. Reduce heat
and simmer for 20 minutes. Mix cottage cheese, ricotta cheese, and parmesan cheese.
3. In an ungreased 9 x 13 pan, layer noodles, cottage
cheese mixture, mozzarella, and meat sauce. Repeat
layers, the meat sauce then mozzarella cheese should be
the last layer.
4. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Allow to cool for 15
minutes before cutting.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake about 40 minutes.
(Pie is done when touched by fingers and does not stick.)

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil pepperoni to remove excess fat for 5 minutes in water to cover, then drain well.
Saute onion in 1 1/2 tablespoons butter until golden brown.

title: barbecue "meat balls"
directions: Freeze tofu overnight and then let thaw.
Crumble and then marinate for 2 to 3 hours in the refrigerator.
Squeeze through cheesecloth or strainer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until well browned.
Place in baking dish and cover with sauce.
Heat thoroughly before serving.

title: dilemma
directions: Mix together butter and flour, like pie crust.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Cool.

title: snicker cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions. Pour half into a 9 x 13 greased pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels, margarine and milk together. Pour over baked cake. Add nuts, chocolate chips and remainder of cake batter and return to oven for another 20 minutes at 350°, then 10 minutes at 325°. Serve with whipped cream, Cool Whip or dust with powdered sugar.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Cook stew beef until almost done with pod of pepper.
Add all other ingredients and salt to taste.
Remove pepper and serve.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Cook chocolate pudding per directions.
After cooked, add cake mix.
Put in greased and floured cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: granny vennie's corn bread dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in bottom of casserole.
Mix with other ingredients and bake until slightly brown.
Do not let dressing get dry!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into two greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan and then remove to a wire rack.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients (be sure to mix thoroughly).
Sift together flour, spices and salt.
Add to oil mixture.
Mix well. Heat applesauce to boiling point.
Mix in baking soda.
Add to oil and flour mixture.
It can be baked in two layer pans and put together with icing or baked in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan or dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Drain. Brown onion and ground beef. Add sauce and simmer 15 minutes. Layer in a buttered 8 x 12-inch baking dish, 1/2 of spaghetti, cheeses, sour cream and sauce. Keep layering until all is gone. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown meat
and onions together.
Add other ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes.
Season to taste.	Freezes well.

title: hot seafood english muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and stir until blended.
Spread over English muffins.
Bake 10 minutes in a 400° oven, then broil until bubbly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients as listed and shape into 2 small loaves in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until loaves begin to brown.
Then pour tomato sauce over top of loaves and return to oven.
Bake until done and sauce thickens (about 30 minutes).

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan and add onion. Beat eggs together.
Add the corns and corn meal mix, then add the melted butter and onion.
Pour into sprayed casserole pan.
Mix sour cream and cheese; add on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: avocado and rice salad
directions: Combine rice, celery, onion, olives, chicken and ham.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon mixture into avocado halves.
Serves 8.

title: jewelry cleaner
directions: Look in the cupboard; close the door.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour.

title: italian meat and spaghetti
directions: Mix all sauce ingredients.
Make ground beef into small balls or add loose to sauce (raw).
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: zucchini carrot bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat together eggs and oil.
Mix in sugar, zucchini, carrots and vanilla.
Gradually mix in flour mixture and finally add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lemony chicken
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook for 6 to 8 minutes, turning once, until lightly brown and no longer pink in center.
Remove to serving platter or dinner plates.
Add chicken broth and lemon juice to skillet.
Stir over medium-high heat 2 to 3 minutes, scraping up any brown bits in pan until sauce is reduced slightly.
Stir in capers and parsley.
Pour over chicken.
Serve over noodles with sauteed bell pepper (green and red) strips.

title: chicken mushrooms bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan. In bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix and pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, for about 1 hour, until tender.
Serve mushroom mixture as gravy.

title: berry batter cake
directions: Line a greased 8 x 8-inch pan with berries.
Beat the next 6 ingredients with mixer for 1 minute.
Pour over berries.
Combine 1/4 teaspoon salt, sugar and cornstarch and blend well.
Pour over batter evenly.
Pour water or juice over all.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Serve by spooning cake upside down and covering with berries.
Dollop with vanilla ice cream while still warm.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Press with fork dipped in milk.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: catfish stew
directions: Fry bacon in heavy pot; add onion and cook until tender.
Pour in water, seasonings and fish.
Bring to boil for a few minutes, then turn heat down and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Butter pan.
Sprinkle bottom with instant rice.
Heat cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups and milk and pour over rice. Arrange chicken over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger (drain) mix and add all ingredients. Bake 1 hour 350 degrees. Pour over fritos.

title: class delight for a good class
directions: Make it.
Take out side for 10 minutes and play.
Let cool for 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana cake
