directions: *You may use sweet milk with lemon or vinegar.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Peel onion and slice over chicken.
Slice apple and place over onion.
Pour barbecue sauce over apple and bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: english peach pie
directions: Skin peaches and slice thin, place in greased 1-1/2 qt. casserole or deep pie plate.

title: crumbed green beans
directions: Heat beans with butter, crumbs, salt and pepper, mixing until beans are coated with crumbs and crumbs are browned.
Garnish with pimiento strips.
Serves 6.

title: black skillet fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla and nuts; bring to a boil for one full minute.
Set skillet aside; cool and add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until it is firm enough to pour into a buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until well blended.
Add pimiento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and cayenne; mix well.
Chill.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in pecans.
May be served with crackers.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Place butter in saucepan.
Add onion, green pepper and celery. Let simmer for a few seconds.
Add remaining ingredients, except ribs.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Brown ribs.
Pour sauce over ribs. Cook at 350° for 2 hours.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts into a ball and spread evenly over 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool. Mix and spoon cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup of Cool Whip over first layer.
Mix pudding and milk until it starts to thicken and pour over second layer.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut or nuts, if desired.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: cinnamon toast cake(makes a great holiday breakfast)
directions: *For a lower fat version, replace the 1/2 c. oil with 1/4 c. oil + 1/4 c. applesauce.

title: sugar-free cocoa frosting
directions: In small mixing bowl, stir together envelope dry whipped topping mix, 1/2 cup cold milk, 1 tablespoon Hershey's cocoa and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract.
Beat on high speed of mixer about 4 minutes or until soft peaks form.

title: spring salad
directions: Drain pineapple, heat the juice to dissolve jello.
Soften cream cheese in microwave, add to jello juice.
Stir.
Combine all together, then fold in Cool Whip last.

title: chocolate cinnamon coffee
directions: Place in coffee maker or percolator basket.
Proceed as if making regular coffee.
Makes 10 cups coffee.

title: crystallized orange nuts
directions: Combine juice and sugar in a 2-quart glass baking dish. Mix well. Stir in pecans. Microwave 6 minutes on High. Stir and continue cooking 8 to 10 minutes on Medium-high or until syrup crystallizes. Separate and cool glazed nuts on a buttered cookie sheet. (Watch carefully while cooking; easy to burn.)

title: mandarin delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or a mold.
Chill until set.

title: three vegetable casserole
directions: Forty-eight hours ahead, grate onion into mayonnaise; refrigerate.
Season with Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce and black pepper.
Refrigerate overnight at least.
Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Drain.
Add mayonnaise mixture.
Top with grated hard-boiled eggs.

title: parmesan vegetables
directions: Slice squash and onion.
Cut bell pepper into 1-inch pieces. Combine all vegetable in a large bowl.
Coat with vegetable cooking spray and toss gently.
Stir fry until tender.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt & pepper.

title: impossible lasagne pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch square or an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in dish.
Mix cooked beef, 1 cup of the Mozzarella cheese, oregano, basil and tomato paste; spoon over top.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour into plate. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cool 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with snipped fresh parsley.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, eggs, applesauce and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in dry ingredients and beat until smooth. Bake at 350° until done, about 50 minutes.

title: grilled catfish
directions: Rinse and dry fillets.
Soak in milk for 20 minutes.
Remove from milk and rinse, removing excess moisture.
Sprinkle with seasoning, rubbing it into meat.
Start grill and place 1/8-inch thick onion slices on grill.
Slice banana peppers and place on top of onion slices.
Place fish on top of onion and pepper. Thinly slice chili peppers and sprinkle over fish.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil.
Grill until easily flaked.
Salt to taste. Serves 4 to 6.
Preparation time:
1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, then flour.
Mash bananas.
Mix in; add nuts.
Put in a well-greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together until fluffy and well blended.
Add sugars and beat well.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift flour and soda together.
Stir into batter until evenly blended.
Add chips and oats.
Stir to combine evenly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on rack.
These cookies freeze well.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: minnesota kraut salad
directions: Make syrup by boiling the sugar and vinegar.
Cool and add celery seed.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples thin.
Fill casserole dish with sliced apples, water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend rest of ingredients with fork until crumbly.
Spread mixture over the top of the apples and bake uncovered in hot oven at 450° for 1 hour or until done.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water.
Boil until it threads.
Add peanuts.
Cook until it turns a golden brown.
Remove from heat. Add salt, butter and soda.
Spread on buttered sheet pan.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Cook the linguine according to package directions.
Saute garlic, olive oil, butter and mushrooms.
Then add and simmer clams and spices.
Add and warm parsley and wine.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: katherine's lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Combine all ingredients listed. Simmer, uncovered, for 50 minutes.

title: couche-couche
directions: Mix salt and sugar in with cornmeal.
Dampen with boiling water.
Let set for a few minutes.
Heat small amount of fat.
Put cornmeal mixture into hot fat and cover the pan.
Stir often over a low fire until couche-couche appears done.

title: arabian delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Sift together flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Beat eggs and add dry ingredients, orange rind, juice, dates and nuts.
Stir gently.

title: basil rice
directions: While frying the hamburger and onion, cook macaroni or spaghetti until tender and drain.
Drain juice off of hamburger and onion.
Put the cooked hamburger into an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan or dish.
Then cover this with catsup.
I put 1 can of peas on one-half of the hamburger and 1 can of corn on the other. (Season with salt and pepper.)
Then add your choice of cheese on top of the casserole and season.
Put in oven and bake about 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In small bowl, mix flour.
In another bowl, combine shortening and sugars.
Cream at medium speed.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour; mix until smooth.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by level tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 1/2 to 5 dozen.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Mix in crab, onion, green pepper, carrot and celery.
Add salad dressing to taste.
Chill overnight. Serve cold.
Do not attempt to freeze.
Stores refrigerated up to one week.
More consistent results obtained with imitation crab.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 2 loaf or 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken lasagna rolls
directions: In bowl, stir eggs, cheese, 1/2 cup parsley, chicken, salt, basil and pepper.
Spread about 1/3 cup cheese mixture on each lasagna noodle.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Cut each roll in half edgewise.
Arrange in single layer in baking dish; spoon sauce over roll-ups.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley.
Serves 8.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat together the flour, butter, sugar, egg yolks, salt, lemon rind and juice. Add the milk; fold in the egg whites whipped stiff. Pour into a deep pie plate lined with crust 1/4 inch thick. Bake 10 minutes in hot oven at 425°, then reduce the heat to 375° and continue baking 30 minutes.

title: potato salad(large bowl)
directions: Beat eggs in pan. Heat over low heat.
Add water and vinegar by spoonfuls.
Add sugar and salt.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Sprinkle Accent and pepper over chicken.
Pour corn oil into 10-inch frypan over medium heat.
Add chicken and saute slowly for about 6 minutes, until white and opaque.
Remove and drain on paper towel.

title: party snack
directions: *Decrease salt, if salted nuts are used.

title: cheesy hamburg casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until slightly tender.
Drain and set aside. Brown hamburg and onions in skillet.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.
Oil a 2-quart casserole dish and spoon in 1/3 of meat mixture.
Add cooked macaroni, then the remainder of meat mixture.
Spread cheese soup over all (may be frozen unbaked). Cover the casserole tightly and bake at 400° until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and hot water until it forms a soft ball (238°).
Add peanuts and butter and stir until it turns golden brown or hard crack (325°).
Remove from heat and stir in soda. Pour on a well-buttered cookie sheet and flatten very thin as quickly as possible.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix with corn bread Stove Top dressing.
Use 1/2 mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Save rest for topping.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream, carrots, onions and squash.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Drain off liquid.
Add spices and cheese and mix until blended.
Spread on rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When hard, may be packed in freezer bags.

title: bacon bits
directions: Cut bacon slices in fourths.
Separate slices.
Combine eggs, vinegar, dry mustard and cayenne pepper.
Keep egg mixture beaten and fluffy.
Dip bacon slices in egg mixture, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Place bacon bits on broiler pan so fat can drain.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Add turkey gravy and heavy cream; bring to boil and let reduce until thick.
Add chopped turkey meat, celery, carrots, peas and mushrooms.
Serve in pie shell with a second shell on top.
Bake until done.
Serves 2.

title: mama's old timey jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; add to mixture.
Add hot water last and mix well. Bake in buttered pan (shallow) for about 20 minutes in 375° oven, then turn out on a damp cloth.
Trim off hard edges.
Spread with jelly and roll quickly.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Wrap in wax paper to hold until set and when set, serve.

title: baked lima beans and tomatoes
directions: Heat margarine in small frying pan.
Brown the onion and bell pepper.
Add tomatoes.
Cook slowly for a few minutes.
Add cooked beans and season to taste.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 450° until slightly browned.
Garnish with crisp bacon.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fun pot roast
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Lay onions on top of roast. Mix beer, chili sauce, sugar and garlic in bowl.
Pour over meat. Cover tightly and cook for 3 1/2 hours at 350°.
Uncover.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add flour and water to juices for gravy.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Scoop out the inside and put into a bowl.
Mix skim milk, Butter Buds and sour cream with potatoes.
Put back into potato shells and sprinkle with fat-free Cheddar.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Mix 1/3 of crab meat with cream cheese.
Roll into a ball. Pat the remaining crab meat around outside of cheese ball.
Place on serving plate and pour cocktail sauce over ball.
Guests can spread on crackers as desired.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown the meat well in a skillet.
In a large casserole dish, combine cabbage, meat, onion and bell pepper; toss to mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup plus 1 cup of water and pour over mixture.
Bake about 1 hour in a 325° oven or until done.

title: pronto picante chicken tacos
directions: In large skillet, cook chicken in hot oil over high heat until no longer pink. Stir in picante; reduce heat to medium and simmer 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally. Heat taco shells as directed on package. Fill each taco shell with about 3 tablespoons of chicken. Top with lettuce, cheese and sour cream. Serve immediately.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions; drain and cool.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Divide nuts and chips in bottom of 2 unbaked pie shells. Combine butter, eggs, sugar and corn syrup. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken over toast
directions: In 8-quart saucepan, boil chicken until tender and remove from heat.
Remove skin from chicken and debone.
Put meat back in broth and add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in medium heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil lined 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with additional nuts if desired.
Chill until firm.

title: kix cereal crisps
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Stir peanut butter, sugars, butter, baking soda, baking powder and egg in large bowl until well mixed. Stir in cereal and chocolate chips.
Shape dough by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls; place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Store loosely covered.

title: melt-in-your-mouth dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast with warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon of sugar and baking powder. Let stand for 20 minutes.
Scald milk.
Add butter, 1/3 cup sugar and salt.
Cool, then add 2 beaten eggs.
Combine all with flour. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 2 hours before serving.
(Shape either as butterhorns or as pinwheels.) Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: frozen corn - no cooking
directions: Mix cold water, sugar and canning salt.
Add to corn.
Bag or box and freeze!
When you are ready to use, cook it like you would fresh.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and let cool.
Add diced cheese, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix well and chill.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook 1/2 hour or until thick on medium heat.
Can as usual.

title: wild rice and chicken
directions: Cook rice according to box directions. Put rice in a square dish. Place chicken on top of rice mixture. Make sure all rice is covered. Pour broth over chicken and rice. Lay bacon over chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all wet ingredients first.
Cream together.
Add dry ingredients.
Refrigerate a day ahead.
May roll out or drop. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: pfeffernuesse cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix honey, sugar, eggs, lard, coffee and anise seed extract together.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
(This makes a soft dough; set aside for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.)
Later make small balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When cookies come out, be ready with brown paper bag with powdered sugar.
Shake a few cookies at a time.
Place out to cool.

title: mince meat
directions: Remove seeds from fruit.
Do not peel.
Grind together all fruits and raisins.
Mix with other ingredients and boil for 2 hours over low heat.
Will be thick and dry when done.
Sterile jars will make 9 pints.

title: mamie eisenhower fudge
directions: Mix evaporated milk, sugar, butter and salt in a saucepan and bring to boiling.
Stir and boil for 7 minutes.
Combine all remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour boiling evaporated milk mixture over all.
Beat until fudge is creamy. Pour batter into 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: seafood stew
directions: In saucepan saute until tender, onion, green pepper, celery, carrots and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients except fish and shrimp and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover and let simmer until potatoes are tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Add fish and shrimp to combine and cook until fish flakes easily, about 7 minutes. Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 18 g, protein 23 g, fat 6 g, calories 217.
One serving = 1/2 bread exchange, 3 protein exchange, 2 vegetable exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: burrito filling
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add tomatoes, green chilies, beans and Tabasco.
Stir to mix and simmer, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with flour tortillas. Garnish with cheese, onion, lettuce, etc.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Spread half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick of butter and 1/2 can of Eagle Brand milk; pour over batter.
Bake cake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Melt 1 stick of butter and the Kraft caramels.
Stir in 1/2 can Eagle Brand milk.
Spread over warm cake, top with 1 cup chopped pecans. Pour remaining batter over cake.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes (don't overbake).
Top with chocolate frosting and sprinkle with 1 cup nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Boil rice until fully cooked.
Saute ham, onion and green pepper in butter.
Add cooked rice, scrambled eggs, soy sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Fry for 5 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat butter and oil in large kettle.
Stir in onions; cook, covered, for about 20 minutes, until onions are transparent. Uncover.
Add salt, garlic and sugar.
Increase heat and continue cooking for 20 minutes, until onions are rich, golden brown. Sprinkle flour over onions, then cook for a few minutes.
Add broth.
Cook, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes on low heat.
Pour soup into individual oven-safe bowls.
Place 1 slice toasted French bread and cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: In a saucepan, heat jelly and mustard; add wieners and heat through.
Serve hot with toothpicks.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves.
Let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Season meat.
Add onion, rice and egg.
Roll a portion of filling into each leaf.
Fasten ends with toothpicks.
Place the cabbage rolls on a rack in pot.
Pour tomato sauce and water over rolls.
Cover and cook for 2 to 3 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Use in layers.
Cover top with remaining bread crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika.
Be sure and salt and pepper as you go. Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: double peanut fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches soft ball (234°).
Remove from heat; add next 4 ingredients.
Stir until well blended; fold in peanuts.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen squares.

title: creamy swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle one side of meat with half the flour and pound in. Turn meat and pound in remaining flour.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown meat.
Transfer pieces to baking dish.
Sprinkle onion soup over meat.
Mix milk and soup; pour over meat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve gravy over meat, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: southern oatmeal pie(tastes like pecan)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried rice
directions: In large skillet cover bottom pan with soy sauce.
Low heat all ingredients except onions.
Saute until soy sauce is mixed well and ingredients hot.
Remove from heat and add chopped onions.

title: betty crocker cocoa chiffon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine boiling water and cocoa.
Let cool.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream sugar and cheese; then add strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Mix by hand.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Then thaw before serving.
Can be frozen for 1 month before using.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Let yeast and water set 2 minutes in large bowl.
Mix eggs, salt, oil and sugar with yeast mixture.
Add 3 cups of flour and beat until smooth.
Then add 2 cups more flour; mix well.
Cover with damp cloth and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Take out and make into rolls (greasing hands).
Muffin tins best.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake following box directions in sheet cake pan. Cut in half. Crumble 1/2 of cake in bottom of large bowl. Spread 1/2 of instant pudding over cake. Next, spread 1/2 of pie filling, 1/2 of pineapple, coconut, nuts and Cool Whip. Crumble remaining half of cake over Cool Whip and repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 2 cups of bran and let stand while assembling other ingredients.
Mix rest of bran with sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Combine all ingredients and bake as needed at 400° for 20 minutes.
Mixture will keep for six weeks or more in the refrigerator.
Dates, raisins, chopped apple, etc. may be added at baking time.

title: turkey ham and wild rice salad
directions: Combine turkey ham and cooled rice mixture in a large bowl. Peel and cube avocados and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Remove seeds from tomatoes and dice.
Mix avocados, tomatoes and green onion with turkey ham and rice.
Combine vinegar, oil and pepper; pour over salad.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put cupcake liners in small muffin pans or on cookie sheet.
Place 2 level tablespoons of brownie batter in each liner.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place one peanut butter candy in center of each cupcake until even with surface of brownie.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes longer.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, with flour. Add sour cream.
Add condensed milk.
Add flavoring of your choice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop on greased cookie sheet and press lightly with a floured fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: french chocolate mousse
directions: In top of double boiler, beat egg yolks and sugar with electric or rotary beater until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in orange liqueur.
Cook over hot, not boiling, water.
Beat constantly, just until hot and mixture thickens slightly (about 10 minutes).
Transfer top of double boiler to pan of cold water and beat until consistency of mayonnaise, 4 or 5 minutes.

title: spareribs, sauerkraut and potatoes
directions: Brown ribs in fat. Season with salt and pepper. Put sauerkraut in bottom of pot and sprinkle with brown sugar. Place ribs and potatoes over sauerkraut, add water. Cover and cook until ribs are tender. Serves 4.

title: fabulous meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine meat, cheese, bread crumbs, onions, carrot, eggs and dressing; mix well.
Place in shallow baking pan and form a loaf.
Cover top with a layer of ketchup.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eggplant stuffing bake
directions: Steam eggplant or boil in salted water for 5 minutes.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Add garlic, eggplant, bread cubes, eggs and seasoning.
Saute for 2 minutes more.
Spoon into a buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Cool, cut and enjoy. (Tastes like Rice Krispies treats, only with peanut butter.)

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Add raisins, nuts and zucchini last.
Spread into jellyroll pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: lillian's cake
directions: Put pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon the pie filling and sugar on top.
Mix nuts with cake mix and sprinkle on top.
Slice the butter and scatter over everything.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, eggs and powdered sugar well. Spread onto cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Prepare beans for cooking according to the master recipe.
In Dutch oven or kettle, cover prepared peas with 5 cups fresh water. Bring liquid to boil; reduce heat to low.
Simmer beans until tender yet still firm, about 40 minutes.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: cocoa drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in the flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Mix in nuts, if desired.
Chill dough at least 1 hour. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto lightly greased sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°, or until almost no imprint remains when lightly touched.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together well.
Add sugar, one cup at a time.
Add one egg at a time, then beat in flour slowly. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Pour mixture into greased tube cake pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: philippine chicken
directions: Put chicken in frypan and cover with mixed liquid.
Cover and simmer about 40 minutes.
Turn chicken several times.
Remove chicken and heat one can of bean sprouts in sauce.
Serve with rice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add first mixture along with the pineapple.
Add carrots, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Turn into unbaked pie shell and bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 40 to 45 minutes longer.
When cool, cover with meringue if desired, or serve with sweetened whipped cream garnished with pecan halves. (Use no substitute for white syrup.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put in a bowl and bake or microwave until vegetables are done. Salt too.

title: herb butter
directions: Cream butter; add chives, sage, parsley and lemon juice.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Put water and yeast into a mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Beat well, then add flour, 1/2 at a time. Knead until smooth. Divide into thirds.
Knead into a ball each. Flatten, then pull and stretch to fit a 9-inch layer cake tin.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Add favorite pizza ingredients, tomato sauce, cheese, etc. Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix boxed corn bread well.
Stir in sour cream, margarine, egg and milk.
Add corn.
Use large, shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: heath bar delight cake
directions: Note:
If you cannot find Heath health bar chips, make your own by crushing regular Heath bars in a plastic bag.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and lemon extract.
Mash bananas and stir into the batter.
Sift dry ingredients together and beat into batter, alternating with buttermilk.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until fork inserted comes out clean.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Beat the eggs until fluffy. Add oil, sugar, vanilla and grated zucchini.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add raisins, pineapple and
nuts.
Blend well. Bake in 2 greased and floured bread pans for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: macaroni chili skillet
directions: In large skillet melt 1 stick margarine.
Add 1 1/2 pounds of ground beef, onion, green pepper and cook until brown.
Add all the other ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sandies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar together.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in the water and the vanilla.
Blend in the flour 1/2 cup at a time. Add the pecans and mix well.
Shape the dough into 1-inch balls. Place them about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 20 minutes.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.
When cookies are cool, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Blend cream and sugar.
Add milk, egg and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 325° and bake 20 minutes.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix together the zucchini, eggs and half of the cheese.
Pat this in a buttered pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Put your choice of meat (ground beef, dried beef or bologna) on top with the onion.
Top this with pizza sauce and sprinkle with cheese. Bake another 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in large frying pan to heat and add macaroni to coat.
Add beef and cook until brown.
Pour off liquid, if any.
Pour on tomato juice and bring to a boil.
Mix in next four ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes or until tender, covered.
Remove cover and put cheese on top and bake 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: mashed potatoes yogurt
directions: Peel and dice potatoes; cook in water until soft.
Drain well. Add all the ingredients and beat with mixer until smooth and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Put popcorn in large, buttered bowl.
Put marshmallows, butter and salt in top of double boiler.
Melt over hot water, stirring constantly.
Pour syrup over corn; stir gently to coat.
Grease hands; quickly shape into balls.
Makes 10.

title: baked country ham
directions: Soak ham overnight in cold water.
Scrub ham with a stiff brush and rinse thoroughly.
Place, skin side down, in a large kettle and cover with cold water.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes per pound.
Add hot water as needed to keep ham covered. Ham is done when shank pulls loose from bone. Remove ham from water and cool, enough to handle.
Remove skin and trim excess fat to a 1/2-inch layer.
With a sharp knife, score fat.

Sprinkle with brown sugar. Add the cup of brown sugar to the juice. Bake ham at 375° about 20 minutes, basting frequently with the juice. Remove to serving platter and garnish with spiced peaches or garnish of your choice.

title: beef casserole
directions: Saute onion, then brown hamburger in skillet.
Add tomato soup, water, beans and noodles.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 25 minutes.
Serve with French bread and tossed salad.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place onions and oil in pan over medium heat.
Saute until translucent.
Add chicken, garlic and rosemary.
Brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add wine and simmer until reduced by half. Add tomatoes.
Cover pan and simmer over low heat.
Cook about 40 minutes until chicken is tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch together, blending well.
Add chocolate flavoring, egg yolks and some milk, only until a paste is formed.
Slowly add rest of milk.
Heat slowly until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool.

title: grandma's corn bread
directions: Mix in a bowl the salt, egg, baking powder and baking soda. Add the corn meal and beat at least 60 times.
Pour into well greased preheated skillet.
Bake 15 minutes in 450 degree oven. Place under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes to brown top.

title: homemade tortillas
directions: *May substitute a portion (like 2 cups) of the flour with whole wheat flour; then might require more water.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs and oil.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add vanilla and zucchini, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients in order given. Bake in loaf pans or tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge turtles
directions: Stir sugar and evaporated milk together.
Bring to boil and boil gently for 9 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips, butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until blended and until chocolate bits are melted.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut when cold.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: old fashion oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes.

title: rozell's best tuna casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add other ingredients. Mix together and bake in a casserole dish for one hour at 350°.

title: morning story muffins
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Set aside.
In another bowl sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture and stir until moistened. Gently fold in carrot, raisins, coconut and raw apple.
Spoon into greased muffin tin to approximately 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Split English muffins into halves.
Spread with sauce.
Cover with cheese and toppings.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: martha washington dipped cream candy
directions: Melt butter and mix ingredients (except chocolate and paraffin) together.
Roll into small balls.
Place on waxed paper.
Chill for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Use toothpick to dip candy balls into chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper to set.
Can be frozen and kept indefinitely.

title: wonder salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Keep in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Jell-O is not dissolved.
Put in dry.

title: lite "unfried" fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in ice water for 20 to 30 minutes before coating.
Coat chicken with yogurt, then shake 2 to 3 pieces in bread crumb/spice mixture (use plastic bag).
Spray jelly roll pan with 3 coats of Pam and place coated chicken on pan.
Spray coat of Pam on chicken before baking.
Bake at 400° on lowest oven rack for 1 hour; turn every 20 minutes to ensure even browning. Leftovers are great for cold sandwiches on Kaiser rolls.

title: chop suey cake(this is delicious)
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add undrained pineapple and rest of ingredients, except nuts and mix well by hand.
Stir in walnuts.

title: curried shrimp and rice(serving size:  6)
directions: Simmer shrimp in 2 1/2 cups water for 4 minutes.
Drain.
Save water.
Saute onion, carrot and celery in butter for 5 minutes. Blend in rice and curry powder.
Add mixture to shrimp water along with ginger and pepper.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Add shrimp and raisins.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Place all seafood in an 8 x 12 glass baking dish.
Mix Lemon Juice, melted Butter; pour over fish.
Spread Sour Cream over fish. Sprinkle Parsley on top.
Cover with grated Cheese.
Preheat oven to 325.
Bake 30 - 35 minutes or until Cheese is golden brown; you'll see juices bubbling in the dish.
Enjoy!
Double this recipe for more than 5 people.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add egg yolks one at a time. Add soda and flour.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Then add coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and beat in last. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add salsa, onions, salt and cream cheese.
Cook until cream cheese is melted.

title: slushy punch
directions: If desired for darker color, you may add a few drops of yellow food coloring.

title: potatoes, sliced and baked
directions: Scrub or peel potatoes.
Cut into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in baking pan; fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt; drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs. Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Use cookie sheet covered with foil and drop this mixture in teaspoonfuls upon it. Put in oven and turn it off.
Keep in oven overnight or at least 4 hours.
Remove cookies with a spatula.

title: bacon poles(microwave)
directions: With scissors, cut bacon strips in half lengthwise, making 2 long strips for each slice.
Wrap one strip in spiral "barber pole fashion" around each bread stick.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together; cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in salt water, drain and slice.
Add green pepper (diced) and onions (diced).
Mix tomato soup, salad oil, vinegar, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over carrot mixture and allow to stand in refrigerator overnight before serving.
Will keep 3 or 4 days.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls onto tinfoil covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes, until edges are browned.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together and enjoy.
Good on Mexican meat loaf!

title: chickpea stew with couscous
directions: Bring chicken or vegetable stock to boil in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add the couscous and salt.
Stir and cover.
After 5 minutes, take off the heat.
Fluff with a fork and re-cover to keep warm.
Peel the sweet potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch cubes. Make sure they are cut small enough or else they won't cook and will hold up the rest of the dish.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg with fork.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add remaining
dry ingredients and blueberries.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana crepes
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and brandy in a 2 c. glass measure.
Microwave at HIGH power for 1 1/2 minutes until butter melts and sugar dissolves and bubbles.
Add quartered bananas and cook covered with wax paper for 2 minutes.
Put crepes in oven to warm - 1 minute on HIGH.
Put 2 scoops of ice cream in each crepe. Fold over placing seam side down.
Pour sauce over crepes and top with whipped cream and slivered almonds.

title: salsa
directions: Drain tomatoes.
Dump everything into a blender.
Whirl it around for a few seconds.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and milk and beat well. Add flour, baking powder and cinnamon which have been sifted together; add raisins and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls two inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add well beaten eggs, cream and pumpkin.
Pour into crust and bake in moderate oven.
Take out when firm.

title: apple cake(moist)
directions: Mix diced apples and sugar together (set aside).
Sift dry ingredients together (set aside).
Add beaten eggs to apple mixture.
Add oil and vanilla; add flour mixture to apple mixture. Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Keep refrigerated after baking.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in round slices in large baking dish. In saucepan, melt oleo.
Add flour and milk.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add bell pepper, pimentos and cheese to sauce.
Let cheese melt.
Pour mixture over potatoes and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: banana puddin'
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, water and pudding; beat until blended. Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Layer cookies, bananas and pudding; repeat.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins in boiling water to cover for 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving 6 tablespoons liquid.
Thoroughly cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Stir flour, salt, soda and spices together.
Mix with oatmeal and add to creamed mixture alternately with raisin liquid.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Will be soft.

title: broccoli and grape salad
directions: Mix broccoli and fruit until well tossed.
In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together and pour over broccoli mixture.

title: melting moments(cookies)
directions: Sift all together and set aside the flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.

title: white cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift baking powder and salt with flour.
Add flour to sugar and butter; add milk.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) round pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter fudge meltaway
directions: Microwave all three ingredients until it is all melted and blended well together.
(One and one-half cups of nuts are optional.)
Pour into greased pan and refrigerate until set and cut into the size pieces you want.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken tender.
Reserve 2 cups broth.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute celery and onion in melted margarine.
Add stuffing mix to celery mixture.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing mixture in bottom of greased, large and shallow baking dish.
Combine chicken with soups and broth.
Pour over stuffing mix.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate drops(cookies)
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler over boiling water and cook 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add coconut, vanilla and nuts.
Drop on greased sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: wednesday shake
directions: In blender, blend all ingredients for a few seconds (you want this shake nice and thick).
Yield:
3 shakes.
Our grandchildren love this one!

title: yummy salad
directions: Combine boiling water, tapioca pudding and orange jello.
Stir well to dissolve.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Set aside until cool.
Stir in Cool Whip and oranges. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Melt butter and cream with sugar in large bowl.
Add egg.
Add yeast (dissolved) to cream mixture, then add flour and stir until well mixed.
Place in airtight bowl and keep in refrigerator.
Drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
The dough will keep several days.

title: german goulash
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside until ready to use.
While noodles are cooking, brown ground beef in large skillet until browned.
Add soup mix, tomatoes and cooked noodles.
Mix well.
Top with grated cheese, cover and heat through until cheese melts.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: sausage ball
directions: Blend together and roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
These can be made ahead of time and frozen in Ziploc bags, then you can just take out what you need.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan (about 9 x 9-inch; I use Corning Ware skillet.)
Add peaches with juice.
Mix sugar, flour and egg and put on top of peaches (mixture will be crumbly).
Cook in 350° oven until crust is light brown (approximately 45 minutes).
It is best when served warm with ice cream or Cool Whip on top.

title: aunt bertha's rice and raisins
directions: Bring rice, water and salt to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer for about 45 minutes.
When water is cooked down, add enough milk to cover rice.
Add raisins and cinnamon.
Cook until raisins are soft.
Serve with more milk and sprinkle with sugar.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add soups.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
When spaghetti is done, add cheese while it's hot, then add remaining ingredients.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt and sugar.
Mix last 3 ingredients together.
Add to flour mixture.
Yield: double crust pie.
Vinegar is the secret to this flakey crust.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs, extracts and flour. Spread batter into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Spoon on pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add mushrooms, spices and sauce. Add cheese.
Spread on hamburger bun.
Top with slice of American cheese and broil until melted.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: To make crust, combine first three ingredients.
Press into 7 x 11-inch baking dish.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Put 2/3 cup of crumbs in a purchased cookie pie crust.
Fill with cooked vanilla pudding.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of leftover crumb mixture. Cool.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with rest of peanut butter mixture.

title: chocolate dream fudge
directions: Mix in large pan first first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a slow boil and boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Add chocolate and chocolate chips and stir until well blended.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour into large pan (about 10 x 15-inches).
Makes 5 pounds.

title: noodle surprise
directions: Stew meat trimmed into bite-size pieces.
Brown in butter. Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Add fresh or canned mushrooms.
Add onions, green pepper; stir and simmer until tender.
Add soup; stir until thickened.
Add milk to consistency you desire.
Boil egg noodles which can be done as meat cooks. Add meat mixture on top of noodles and serve.

title: dijon-cream sauce
directions: Combine oil and vinegar in a cup; rub onto beef.
Season generously with salt.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Coarsely crush peppercorns and mustard seed in a blender or food processor or by hand with a mortar and pestle.
Roll beef in crushed mixture, pressing into the surface to coat.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sauce.
Mix well.
Make into balls.
Put on cookie sheet.
Put in oven heated to about 450° (ovens may vary) until grease is out, then put in pot with sauce and cook for about 30 minutes to 45 minutes.
Enjoy by itself or with spaghetti.

title: heath bar imitators
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and cover with a layer of saltine crackers.
Boil butter and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Spread over saltines and bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over crackers.
Let stand a few minutes. Spread chocolate over crackers.
Refrigerate until hard.
Remove foil and break into pieces.

title: sausage snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Serve hot.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: quesadillas
directions: Cut flour tortillas into fourths.
Lay 1/2 on cookie sheet. Place Monterey Jack cheese, onion, sour cream and hot sauce on each quartered flour tortillas.
Place other 1/2 of quartered tortillas on top.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Top with tomatoes, lettuce and shredded cheese.

title: chess cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: watermelon rind pickle
directions: Cut all pink from rind, soak in Lilly lime 12 hours using enough water to cover rind well.
Next morning, wash rind well and scatter a handful powdered alum over rind, cover with scalding water and let stand 10 minutes.
Rinse and boil 1/2 hour in clear water.
Take out of water and let cool.
Boil 1/2 hour in strong ginger tea, using root ginger.
Weigh rind and make syrup.
For 8 pounds rind, make syrup using remaining ingredients (tie spices in bag).
Cook until tender enough to pierce with toothpick and has an amber color.
(I put a piece of ginger from the tea and a little piece of cinnamon in each jar.
This is not enough syrup to cover rind, but I like the crystallized effect it has when not entirely covered.)

title: old fashion molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt. Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg and molasses; mix well. Add dry ingredients to the mixture alternately with water, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Drop heaping teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add pineapple, flour and baking powder.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in layers or loaf pan.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: In large saucepan heat butter and add onions until soft.
Stir in diced potatoes and carrots, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Stir in fish, then milk.
Simmer gently for 15 to 20 minutes.
Season as desired.

title: rice artichoke salad
directions: Drain liquid from artichokes.
Add to salad dressing and curry powder.
Set aside.
Chop artichokes, green pepper, olives, pimento and green onions.
Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions on package.
Add chopped ingredients and salad dressing. Chill overnight.
To make main dish, add cubed cooked chicken breasts.
Serves 12.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread with chocolate chips.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces almond bark in 2-quart bowl on High for 2 minutes; stir.
Continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Separate eggs and set egg whites aside.
Mix sugar and egg yolks with electric mixer.
Add buttermilk.
Mix well. Sift flour and baking soda together.
Add flour and oil, about one third at a time, into the sugar mixture.
Make sure flour is the last ingredient added.
Add vanilla, red food coloring and vinegar. With clean beaters, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Spoon into three 9-inch cake pans sprayed with nonstick baking spray.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of the cake pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter and cream for about 10 minutes on medium heat.
Pour in marshmallow cream and crunchy peanut butter.
Mix well and pour into greased pans.
Cool, then cut.

title: party almonds
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, slowly saute the almonds in butter about 6 to 7 minutes or until golden; drain off excess butter.
In small bowl, combine celery salt, chili powder and ground red pepper; toss almonds in mixture until well coated. Spread almonds on foil to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Wash and separate cauliflower into very small flowerets and put into large kettle.
Add water and salt.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer until very tender.
Add bouillon cubes and butter. Bring to boil.
Stir in Cream of Wheat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Salt to taste.

title: bean salad
directions: Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Line
casserole
dish	with
crushed
saltines.
Slice onions and
cook until tender, not brown, in melted margarine. Layer onions
and undiluted mushroom soup.
Beat eggs and milk together. Pour
over onions and soup.
Top with grated cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: cheese danish
directions: Spread out 1 package of crescent rolls and flatten slightly. Mix together the cream cheese, 1 egg yolk, sugar and vanilla. Spread this mixture on top of crescent rolls.
Spread other package of crescent rolls on top of this.
Baste top with other egg yolk.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool and slice.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a bowl, blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover; chill for 12 hours.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown hamburg (drain if too fatty).
Add tomato juice and water.
Add bay leaf, sliced carrots, sliced celery, sliced onion, sliced garlic, salt and hot sauce and bouillon cubes.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add corn, beans, and spinach. Cook until spinach is thawed.
About 15 minutes to 1/2 hour before serving, add noodles.

title: pat's tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients except shells.
Divide the mix evenly on each shell.
Spread out, then roll up the tortillas.
Slice into 3/4 inch slices with an electric knife.
Rolls can be wrapped tightly and frozen.
Thaw slightly and slice.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, ginger, nutmeg and orange juice.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in butter. Pour over hot carrots; stir to coat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips with almond bark.
Add peanuts.
Spoon onto waxed paper and chill until hardened.
Quick, easy and delicious!

title: cheese ring
directions: Grate cheeses and onion.
Mix all ingredients except pecans. Place in ring mold or form 2 cheese balls.	If balls, roll in pecans; if ring, pat with pecans.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, strawberries and nuts. Blend well.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: good dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients to make soft dough.
Divide into two parts.
Roll very thin and let dry 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into strips or 2-inch squares and drop into simmering chicken broth. Cook until done or 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kahlua mousse
directions: In large bowl, combine the Cool Whip, coffee, cocoa and sugar, blending well. Fold in Kahlua. Spoon into sherbet dessert glasses. Place a piece of Saran Wrap over dessert glasses until ready to serve.

title: angie's texas size chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Add sugar, eggs, corn syrup and vanilla; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Line 2 pizza pans with foil; spread batter in pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from oven.
Let cookies cool in pans.
When cool, remove foil and place back in pan or on a plate.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter and oleo; spread 1/2 of onion mixture on bottom of dish; then all the macaroni, all cheese and all mashed potatoes.
Top with other half of onion mixture.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 3/4 hour.

title: apple punch
directions: Add cinnamon to taste.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut each potato into 8 lengthwise wedges (64 wedges).
Mix together all ingredients, except wedges.
Line a jelly roll pan with foil and brush lightly with oil mix.
Arrange potatoes, peel side down, on foil.
Brush with oil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until brown and tender.
Brush with oil during baking.

title: mounds cake
directions: Mix and bake.
Let cool completely, then split the layers.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: Combine soup and milk.
In shallow baking dish arrange broccoli and chicken.
Top with 1/2 of soup mixture then add the stuffing mix and add the last of soup to top of chicken and broccoli.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, then place under broiler for a few minutes to make the stuffing lightly brown.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: In a large bowl, combine cottage cheese and Bleu cheese crumbles.
Mash with fork until reduced to tiny lumps. Add all ingredients.
Whip with fork.
Refrigerate overnight before using. Shake before using.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Swirl into batter.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Check after 40 minutes with toothpick.

title: mom's busy day roast
directions: Place roast in foil.
Cover surface of meat with soup mix. Put vegetables on top.
Dot with butter, then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Seal tightly and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices and milk; beat.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 50 more minutes.
Cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. In a large mixing bowl, add oil, diced tomatoes and green chilies and diced tomatoes. Toss lightly. Serving Size: 1 1/2 cups.
Servings Per Container: 8.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute bacon, onion, celery and garlic; stir in broth, soup, water, tomatoes and macaroni.
Simmer 15 minutes; add cabbage, salt and zucchini.
Cook 10 minutes or until done.

title: french love cakes
directions: Beat butter, sugar, vanilla and salt with mixer until fluffy. Stir in flour and pecans until combined.
Shape into 1/4-inch balls; flatten slightly with bottom of glass dipped in granulated sugar.

title: cheesy cauliflower
directions: Wash head of fresh cauliflower and remove stems and just enough of stalk to leave head intact.
Boil cauliflower until done.
(Could be cooked in microwave.)
Mix mustard, mayonnaise, lemon pepper and cheese.
Spread over cauliflower and heat in oven until cheese melts.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: country fried grilled potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half; slice approximately 1/4-inch thick, leaving skin on.
Cut margarine in slices; place half on bottom of an 8 x 10-inch aluminum pan.
Spread potatoes out.
Sprinkle with onion and peppers; place rest of margarine over it.
Cover with tinfoil and place on grill.
Occasionally remove foil and gently roll potatoes over until slightly brown.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl, using fingertips or electric mixer. Form quickly into a ball and wrap in plastic wrap or wax paper. Chill in refrigerator 2 to 24 hours.
Roll out and line pie tins and bake as directed for pie recipe.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 c. melted butter and sugar.
Press into 9 X 13 inch utility dish.
Beat eggs, 1 c. butter and powdered sugar with mixer for 15 minutes.
Spread bottom layer.
Cover with bananas, nuts, and pineapple.
Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.
Serves 20.

title: low-fat pumpkin roll
directions: Beat egg product at high speed until light and fluffy (about 2 minutes).
Beat in sugar; add oil, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Beat at low speed until combined.
Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice and salt and add to pumpkin mixture.
Beat at low speed just until combined.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick spray coating.
Line with waxed paper.
Pour batter into the pan and spread evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients until just blended.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all in pan; let boil 20 minutes, then put in hot jar. Makes about 8 pints.

title: spinach dip
directions: Make dip the night before.
Cut off top of bread.
Hollow out; cut into cubes and fill with dip.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bring first 7 ingredients to a boil, stirring.
Pour into baked shell.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: glorified rice
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water.
You can use the juice drained from pineapple for part of the water.
When gelatin begins to set, add rice and pineapple and fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Can be made into cupcakes also.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat eggs first, then add sugar, sweet potatoes, butter, vinegar and salt.
Mix until well blended and pour into thawed pie shells.
Bake at 350 degrees until firm.
Recipe can be doubled if necessary. Helpful hint: Place frozen pie shells in oven the night before to thaw.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg in a large bowl.
Stir in milk, can of corn with sweet peppers and 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add and beat in flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.

title: better than ? cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in a large cake pan (14 1/2 x 10 x 2-inches).
Spread pineapple over cake.
(Do not drain.) Allow to cool.
Mix pudding (according to directions on box) and spread over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Add coconut, nuts and whatever.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together first
ingredients
and put into baking pan. Mix soup and 2 cups chicken broth; pour over chicken and rice. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat pizzas
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, onion and peppers in a bowl. Toast muffins in a toaster.
Place muffins on a cookie sheet and spoon mixture on each muffin.; then top with both cheeses.
Place in a 400° oven until cheese is melted.

title: hawaiian fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350°.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla, butter and cream cheese for frosting.

title: mrs. ostrand's marinated vegetables
directions: Mix marinade and pour over vegetables in large bowl; let it sit overnight in refrigerator.
Stir or shake occasionally. Arrange on platter.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool and crumble.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Layer 1/2 of cake crumbs and 1/2 of pineapple, pie filling, whipped topping and nuts in bowl. Repeat for second layer.

title: cherry nut salad
directions: Pour all into large mixing bowl except nuts.
Mix well.
Add nuts.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and microwave 8 minutes.
Serve on spaghetti.
Adjust spices to taste.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at high speed for 5 minutes or until light and fluffy.
If too stiff, add a few drops of milk until it reaches the right consistency.

title: uncooked cranberry apple relish
directions: Put orange and cranberries through coarse chopper.
Use blender and do a quarter of mixture at a time.
Stir in remaining ingredients, cover and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: asian chicken wings
directions: Mix together.
Marinate chicken wings in mixture for 1 hour. Place in 350° oven until golden, about 40 minutes.

title: almond tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Allow to steep for 15 minutes.
Add sugar.
Stir to dissolve.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon slice.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and vanilla.
Gradually add both sugars and cream mixture until fluffy.
Add eggs in thirds, beating well each time.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add by fourths to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Stir in nuts and rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: cereal mix
directions: Heat until melted butter, sugar and garlic salt.
Divide cereals into 2 large pans.
Pour melted butter mixture evenly into two pans.
Bake in oven at 250° for one hour, turning every 15 minutes.
Last 10 minutes add kaki mochi.
Cool on paper towel.

title: cheese fritters
directions: Boil the potatoes; drain and keep hot.
Whip the egg yolks with the cream and mix the potatoes, cheese and various seasonings.
Beat the egg whites and fold them into the mixture. Drop one tablespoon at a time into a deep fat fryer and fry until golden brown and crispy.

title: easy chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix together soups, milk and rice.
Place on bottom of ungreased casserole.
Top with chicken.
Sprinkle with package of dry onion soup.
Cover with double aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce, 1/2 cup water, mustard, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: fish fillet bake
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Stir in rice and cook until rice turns golden brown.
Then add tomatoes (cut tomatoes in half lengthwise), pepper and garlic; simmer slowly.
Place fish in bottom of buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spoon rice mixture over fish fillets.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 400° oven 45 to 55 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: ice molds - stars a-blazin'
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Add few drops food coloring.
Pour into molds or ice cube trays.
(Use small star shaped molds or any molds to float in punch bowl and ice cubes for individual punch cups.)
Freeze solid.
Unmold just before serving.

title: nut cluster cups
directions: Melt chocolate chips with shortening in top of double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat; stir in pecans.
Spoon heaping teaspoonfuls into 1-inch paper candy cups or paper-lined mini muffin cups, filling each half full.
Chill until firm.
Peel off paper cup, if desired.
Makes 14 to 16 cups.

title: oatmeal toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add next 3 ingredients; blend well. Press mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over bars; spread when softened.
Cool completely before cutting.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen bars.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix apples, sugar, cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon salt and nutmeg.
Turn into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Mix syrup, water and 2 tablespoons margarine; pour over apple mixture. Mix flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cut in shortening.
Sprinkle in milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing until all flour is moistened and pastry almost cleans sides of bowl.
Gather pastry into ball; shape into flattened round on lightly floured surface.
Roll pastry to fit top of casserole; brush with 3 tablespoons margarine.
Bake 30 minutes; remove from oven.
Cut crust with sharp knife into small pieces, mixing into apple filling.
Bake until apples are tender and pieces of crust are golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in the butter.
Add salt and flour and blend thoroughly.
Add soup and a little milk to make a smooth paste.
Add rest of milk.
Continue stirring until smooth sauce.
Take off heat and add tuna fish and lemon juice.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: lemon delight
directions: Chill Milnot (put in freezer 1 hour).
Mix and set 1 package lemon Jell-O, 2/3 cup sugar and boiling water.
Whip Milnot.
Add lemon juice and whip until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Whip Jell-O until frothy.
Stir Jell-O and Milnot mixture together.
Pour over graham cracker crust and allow to set at least 5 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken; don't salt.
Pick off bones.
Set aside.
Save broth.
Melt margarine and stir into dressing.
In greased dish (13 x 9-inches), put layer of dressing, layer chicken.
Mix mushrooms and chicken soup with broth.
Pour over layers.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 1 hour.

title: marge's unbeatable brownies
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, butter and chocolate.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt, mixing after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for metal pan or 325° for glass pan for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test to see if done by using the toothpick test.
Let cool for 45 minutes before cutting.

title: chunky chicken chili
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
On wax paper, toss chicken with flour.
In large skillet over medium-high heat cook chicken in oil 5 to 7 minutes until brown.
Add onion and cook 3 minutes until tender.
Stir in jalapeno peppers and next 5 ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes until cheese is melted and chili is heated through.
Serve over warm cornbread.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together, add all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into paper-lined tube cake pan.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: sugar-free ribbon salad(grandma's favorite for christmas)
directions: Add 2 packages Jell-O to 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 3/4 cups cold water.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.
When firm, mix in another bowl the lemon Jell-O and boiling water.
Add pineapple. Cool slightly.
Then add cream cheese (beat until smooth).
Add whipped topping and mayonnaise.
Pour over lime gelatin.
Next, dissolve cherry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water and 1 3/4 cups cold. When syrupy, pour over set up lemon.
Refrigerate.

title: tortilla spirals
directions: Let cream cheese soften for 15 to 20 minutes, then mix cream cheese with olives, cheese and green onions in a small bowl. Spread mixture onto a tortilla and roll tortilla tightly (repeat with all tortillas).
Cover rolled tortillas with a wrap or foil and place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Slice tortillas into spirals and place on a circular plate with picante sauce as a dip.

title: no fat split pea soup
directions: Rinse split peas and soak for 1 hour.
In large pot, put split peas in 8 cups of water.
Chop onions, garlic and carrots and mix in the pot.
Finely chop parsley and dill.
Add with the remaining seasonings.
Cook 2 hours on medium heat.
Add water to thin if needed.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Cherries or peanut butter may be substituted.

title: jello orange salad
directions: Make Jell-O with 1 cup of liquid (using 1/2 cup juice from oranges and 1/2 cup hot water).
Let cool.
Add sherbet; mix real good.
Add Cool Whip, then oranges.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook onions with beef; drain.
Pour into large
casserole
x
13-inch or larger).
Place Tater Tots on top of ground beef.
Cover Tater Tots with soup.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Great covered with sliced cheese or Cheez Whiz.

title: lemon jello
directions: Prepare jello with water and juice; let stand until it begins to thicken.
Chill canned milk; whip and add sugar.
Then add lemon juice and whip.
Spread dish with graham cracker crumbs. Pour in mixture and top with more crumbs.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sifted together, stir in flour and soda.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add potato chips (crushed) and chopped nuts to the other ingredients. Mix well.

title: hearty chicken soup
directions: In large saucepot, combine chicken broth, carrots, celery and rice.
Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Add cooked chicken and parsley to taste.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: cucumber and yogurt dip
directions: Wash cucumber well.
Grate unpeeled cucumber.
Drain cucumber very well until almost dry.
Combine with other ingredients.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Cream the cheese until smooth.
Stir in Eagle Brand and pudding mix.
Fold in half of the whipped topping.
Layer in a dish the pudding, cookies and bananas.
Top with remaining topping.
Chill.

title: baked rice
directions: Brown rice in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add green onions and cook lightly.
Stir in broth and wine.
Pour into large casserole dish. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Dot top of rice casserole with butter.
Cover and bake at 375° until fluffy.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Cut up meat and brown in hot shortening.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Add noodles last.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Add pecans. Roll into balls and bake in 350 degree oven for 15 minutes.
Roll in 10X sugar while hot.

title: cobb salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces in large salad bowl. Combine lettuce with watercress.
Arrange wedges of tomatoes and avocado slices around edge of bowl.
Spoon chicken into center of bowl.
Arrange egg slices around chicken.
Sprinkle bacon, Blue cheese and chives over all.
Use Fresh Lemon Dressing.

title: fruit sticks
directions: Chop fruit, nuts and dates; add milk to this mixture.
Put brown paper in an oblong pan and grease well.
Bake at 270° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out onto waxed paper on which powdered sugar has been sprinkled.
Cut in strips. Roll in more powdered sugar if desired.

title: grandma's million dollar pie
directions: Stir together milk, lemon juice, crushed pineapple, 4 ounces of Cool Whip and nuts.
Pat into a graham cracker crust.
Let chill.
Top with remainder of the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill before serving.

title: texas chili
directions: *Add bacon, crumbled, to chili.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef; drain.
Add sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Separate biscuit dough into 12 biscuits.
Place one biscuit in each of 12 greased muffin cups, pressing dough up sides of each cup.
Spoon meat into cups. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: puff pastry with ham filling
directions: Heat butter and water.
When mixture is boiling, add flour all at once and stir vigorously until mixture no longer sticks to sides of pan.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Drop by tablespoons onto a well-greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 minutes longer. Remove from baking sheet and cool.
When ready to serve, cut open one side and fill.

title: melon salad
directions: Cut watermelon in half lengthwise leaving one inch in center crosswise to look like a basket, then scoop out and remove seeds. Scoop into melon balls.
Put in a 5-quart container, then cut cantaloupe in half and scoop out into balls and put in container. Add blueberries, refrigerate at least an hour.
When ready to serve, peel and slice bananas.
Mix with the rest of the fruit, pour into hollowed out watermelon.

title: quick gourmet pizza
directions: Spread pizza sauce onto tops of pita bread.
Sprinkle chunks of Feta cheese, grated Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese on top.
Top with chopped Calamata olives, sun-dried tomatoes, artichoke hearts, pressed garlic and chopped, fresh basil.
Cook in preheated oven at 400° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients together in a jar with a tight fitting lid. For each cup of tea, mix 2 heaping tablespoonfuls in a cup and fill cup with boiling water.
Stir.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and egg. Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Alternate with the fruit juice. When combined add raisins, pecans and apples.
Fold in.
Pour into three small loaf pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm right from pans.

title: pigs out of the blanket
directions: Prepare rice (cook); saute ground beef, onion and bacon bits (brown).
Stir in soup and water; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Alternate layers of cut cabbage and ground beef mixture in a casserole.
Bake covered at 375° for 1 hour or until cabbage is cooked.

title: cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk; add meat, eggs and seasonings.
Add cubed cheese and green peppers.
Mix well and form into a loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix sour cream, coconut and marshmallows.
Fold in drained fruits and mix.
Set in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: indian fried rice
directions: Cook and stir rice and onion in butter until rice is yellow and onion is tender.
Stir in raisins, bouillon, curry powder and salt.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Stir in water. Cover and bake in 350° oven until liquid is absorbed, 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir in almonds.
Serve with chicken or lamb.
Serves 6.

title: granny's meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg white and sugar until stiff peaks form (it takes a long time).
Add chopped nuts and drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: russian cuttletta sauce
directions: Saute onions in oil until clear.
Add carrots.
Saute until soft.
Add flour and stir.
Add chopped tomatoes and paste (or small can of tomato paste).
Stir.
Top off with enough water to fill the skillet, leaving room for stirring.
Add parsley, salt and pepper and basil to taste.
Simmer until thick.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cover and let boil for one minute to allow steam to wash down crystals that cling to sides of pan.
Uncover pan and cook, using candy thermometer to 236° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and peanut butter and beat until candy begins to thicken and lose its high gloss.
Turn into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan (buttered) and cut.

title: apple oatmeal bars
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Mix brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut in Crisco until crumbly.
Put layers in 8 x 9-inch pan.
Put half of mixture in bottom of pan, applesauce in center and mixture on top.
Bake in hot oven at 375° until brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all until blended.
Add nuts and chill.

title: chocolate filled bonbon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg and extracts.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nuts. Mix until blended.

title: texas chili
directions: Fry bacon in 4-quart Dutch oven over medium heat until crisp. Remove bacon with slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.
Brown half of beef cubes in pan drippings.
Remove and brown other half. Saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in pan drippings until tender (about 5 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients including beef and bacon.
Cook over high heat to a boil, about 7 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer approximately 1 hour until meat is tender.

title: microwave hot pizza casserole
directions: Use Saran Wrap to cover dish during microwaving.
Microwave meat 4 to 5 minutes on High.
