Using a colander, drain off grease. Microwave onion and green pepper together on High for 2 minutes. Combine all the ingredients, except cheese.
Mix well and microwave on High for 18 to 20 minutes, stirring halfway through. Let stand covered for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Recover and microwave until cheese has melted.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except the catsup, steak, barbecue or chili sauce together thoroughly. Spread the catsup over top, if desired.

title: beef tacos
directions: Crumble ground beef into 4 cup measure.
Cover loosely and microwave on High (100%) until very little pink remains, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Break up and drain.
Stir in onion, chilies, salt, cumin and garlic.
Microwave uncovered until hot and onion is tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Toss avocado and lemon juice; stir avocado and tomato into beef mixture.
Spoon into taco shells.
Top with sour cream and cheese.
Serve with taco sauce if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie; bake 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookie at 375°.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: ritzy apple pie
directions: Bring boiling water, white sugar and cream of tartar to a boil in a saucepan.
Add crackers and cook 2 minutes.
Do not stir. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon; dot with butter.
Put on top crust and bake 10 minutes at 425°; reduce to 325° and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: Mix crushed cookies and butter; press into bottom of 9-inch spring form pan.
Bake at 325 for 10 minutes (Bake at 300 degrees for 10 minutes if using a dark nonstick spring form pan).

title: basic strada with variations
directions: Remove crusts.
Butter each slice, place six slices of bread, butter side down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese slices. Repeat layers.
Put grated cheese on top.
Pour milk and egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate four hours or overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350° and let stand 20 minutes before serving.
Makes 15 servings.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender or quart jar.
Blend or shake until frothy.

title: western barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Cook and drain the ground beef.
Cut peppers in quarters.
Mix onion, beef, ketchup, rice and soy sauce together.
Grease casserole dish and line dish with bell peppers.
In center, fill with beef mixture and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven off and cover meat dish with cheese.
This dish needs to be covered so as not to dry out.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sugar-free chocolate cream pie
directions: Make the pie crust.
Bake and cool completely.
Make up the pudding using the milk.
Pour into the cooled crust.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Make up whipped topping according to package instructions.
Spread on top of the pie and serve.

title: spice bars
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with coffee.
Put in greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: dirt pie(yields 1 pie)
directions: Pour milk into bowl, add pudding mix and beat with a wire whisk until well blended.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping, stir in 1 cup cookies and rocks into pudding mixture. Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle remaining cookies.
Freeze about 4 hours, then serve.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In small saucepan, mix cornstarch and water.
Add next 6 ingredients and boil until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Brush raw chicken with this glaze.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes, brushing with glaze every 10 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Bake 30 minutes more, brushing occasionally.
Add drained canned pineapple during last 10 minutes of baking.

title: spicy squash bake
directions: Steam squash 10 to 12 minutes, until tender.
Cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in salsa, salt and pepper. Gently stir in squash.
Place 1/2 squash mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese.
Top with remaining squash, then cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Ways in one stick of margarine. Cream sugar and one stick of margarine. Add eggs, flour, and soda alternately with buttermilk. Add melted candy mixture and nuts. Bake in 3 9 inch pans at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. Frost with Milky Way Icing.

title: creole fish orleans
directions: In a large skillet melt margarine; saute onion, celery and garlic 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, bay leaf, Worcestershire, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes or until thickened.
Add mushrooms.
Roll fillets.
Arrange in sauce.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer or until fish is done.
Remove bay leaf.
Remove fish to serving platter.
Spoon sauce around fish.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Can be served over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: quick danish
directions: Note: The rolls may be prepared ahead, covered and refrigerated up to 2 hours. Bake as directed.

title: ann's chicken casserole
directions: Layer cooked and cut chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Melt butter or margarine, add crushed crackers and top casserole. Bake at 325° until heated thoroughly, about 40 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: california dream bars
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Press mixture firmly in bottom and sides of ungreased baking pan (7 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 1 1/2 inches).
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: In large baking dish, take 1/2 package Doritos and crush in bottom of Pyrex casserole dish.
Mix cans of soup and Ro-Tel and pour over chips.
Spread onion.
Add chicken and cubed Velveeta cheese and put on top.
Spread crushed chips over all.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: sauteed scallops with garlic
directions: Wash and dry scallops and shake them in flour.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Add scallops and cook them very quickly, tossing them in the oil so that all sides are browned.

title: corn and corn muffins(two versions of corn make these muffins doubly good)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stir until blended.
Fill large greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for 12 to 15 minutes or until muffins are brown. Makes 10 to 12 large muffins.

title: hazel's stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers until partially tender.
Brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain and mix with rice, salt and pepper.
Stuff peppers.

title: easy meat dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook until done.

title: chicken sandwiches
directions: Make about 50 sandwiches with mayonnaise.
Then eat them.

title: cajun chili
directions: Cook beef, onion, pepper, garlic and seasonings until beef is lightly browned. Add remaining ingredients. Cover. Cook over low heat 1 hour. Stir often. Uncover and cook to desired consistency. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine and mix first 6 ingredients in order.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Combine quickly, but gently, the ice cream, pumpkin, sugar and spices.
Spread into crust.
Freeze until firm (1 hour or overnight).
Serve with whipped topping.

title: fricadillies
directions: Beat the egg.
Add the milk and bread crumbs; let soak.
To the hamburger, add salt and pepper to season.
Add this to milk and bread mixture; mix.
Shape hamburger mixture into small patties; brown in the butter in a skillet.
Put in casserole.
Put the mushroom soup and water in skillet with butter; stir until hot.
Pour over patties.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour or longer.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Place vegetables in a small colander or strainer; drain well. Beat together cream cheese and lemon juice until smooth.
Stir in vegetables and pepper.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: pineapple bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat sugar and margarine or butter until blended.
Increase speed to high; beat until light and fluffy, about 10 minutes.
Reduce speed to low.
Add flour and remaining ingredients.
Beat until well mixed, constantly scraping bowl.
Increase speed to high; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: macaroni and cheese(for "seniors")
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender; drain off water. Combine melted margarine and flour over low heat.
Heat milk in a large saucepan. Add the fat/flour mixture.
Stir thoroughly until blended. Add the macaroni; simmer until mixture begins to thicken. Add shredded cheeses and salt. Simmer until cheeses melt.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: apple chuckles
directions: Slice apples vertically into 1/2-inch slices.
Remove seed. Sprinkle on lemon juice to keep apples from turning brown.
Spread 1/4-inch layer of peanut butter on one side of each slice.
You will need two slices for each Chuckle.
Nestle 4 marshmallows into peanut butter and a slice.
Place another slice of apple, peanut butter side down, on top of the marshmallows.
Press the two slices gently together.

title: white zin raspberry fooler
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir and serve with a smile.

title: blueberry spice topping
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg together in a bowl. Gradually stir in the hot water and lemon juice.
Cook to boil and then gradually add blueberries and bring to a boil.
Great on pancakes or on top of vanilla ice cream.

title: easy french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, add onions and saute until lightly browned (about 5 minutes).
Add water, bouillon, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Pour soup into broiler safe bowls, break 1 slice of bread into large cubes and float on top of soup (1 slice for each bowl of soup). Place cheese on top of each bowl.
Place under broiler until cheese bubbles and browns slightly.
This is the easiest "homemade" soup I've ever made!

title: cajun chicken strips
directions: In a large Ziploc bag, combine flour, poultry seasoning, garlic salt, paprika, pepper and cayenne pepper. Add chicken and shake to coat. In a large skillet, cook chicken in butter for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp in lemon butter
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Cook over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Serve with wild rice.

title: spinach brownies
directions: Cut zuchini lengthwise. Scoop out inside to within 1\4 inch of skin. Dice the insides with onion, peppers and mushrooms. Saute in frying pan to slightly tender. Add tomato sauce and croutons. Refill shells, sprinkle with cheese. (your choice).
Put in lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 20-25 min., until tender and cheese is melted.

title: beef pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into 1/4-inch slices.
Toss with cornstarch in large bowl until coated.
Saute beef a few slices at a time, in 1/4 cup of the oil in a wok until no pink remains, about 3 minutes. Remove meat as it cooks to a warm platter.
Saute peppers, onions and garlic in remaining oil until tender, about 3 minutes.
Return meat to wok.
Stir in soy sauce and water.
Continue cooking, stirring and scraping brown bits in wok, until sauce thickens.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil. Cook until reduced to half. Add honey. Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients, stirring well. Cover and chill overnight. Keep refrigerated when not in use.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Line pie pan or casserole dish with chips.
Layer meat, beans, sour cream, onion, olives and cheese.
Warm in oven until cheese is melted.

title: whole wheat popovers
directions: Position rack in lower third of oven.
Preheat oven to 450°. Grease 6 (6-oz) custard cups.
Set custard cups in jelly roll pan for easier handling; set aside.
Beat eggs in large bowl with electric mixer at low speed 1 minute.
Beat in milk and butter until blended.
Beat in flours and salt until batter is smooth. Pour evenly into prepared custard cups.
Bake 20 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 15 minutes; quickly make small slit in top of each popover to let out steam.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove from cups.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes. Serve warm or cool completely.
Makes 6 popovers.

title: veal bordelaise
directions: In a Dutch oven, heat the butter and brown the meat well on all sides.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for about 2 hours, until the meat is tender.
Cut the meat into thin slices.
Serve it surrounded by the vegetables and with the gravy on the side.

title: angel hair amatriciana
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon just until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain fat from skillet.
Add corn oil.
Heat over medium heat.
Add onion; saute 6 to 8 minutes or until browned.
Stir in tomatoes with juice, breaking tomatoes with spoon.
Add bacon, cider vinegar, sugar, salt and crushed red pepper.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Toss with angel hair.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple chip squares
directions: Beat in one bowl the eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with the egg mixture.
Peel 5 medium apples and grate them, then add to batter.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts on top and chocolate chips on top of nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strata
directions: Cook bacon and sausage.
Chop in small pieces and mix together.
Set aside.
Put half of bread cubes in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Cover with half of cheese, then half the bacon and sausage mixture.
Repeat; set aside.

title: ranch stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat with onion until done.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in dry Ranch dressing mix.
Add fresh tomatoes and cooked rice.
Let cool while preparing peppers, then add sour cream.

title: chocolate dipped bananas
directions: You will need 8 wooden sticks.

title: easy chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into approximately 1-inch squares.
Combine all dry ingredients and mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in butter, then in dry mixture.
Coat well. Place chicken pieces on baking sheet which has been covered with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: fast and fabulous dessert
directions: Open can of pie filling (your choice) and place on top of angel food cake.
Let it run down sides of cake.
Place Cool Whip on top and nuts.
Looks fantastic and tastes even better. Low-fat!

title: zesty snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, mix cereals, pretzels and snack crackers. Pour into large baking pan, 15 x 10 x 1, ungreased.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over cereal mix.
Toss to coat. Bake at 225° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes. Store in airtight containers.

title: moroccan pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and granulated sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla, raisins and nuts.
Pour 3/4 of batter into a 10-inch tube pan lined on bottom with waxed paper.
Mix remaining batter with cocoa and cinnamon and spoon onto batter in pan.
Run a knife through batter to marbleize.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes, then turn out on rack; peel off paper.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Break up bread slices real fine and break eggs into it.
Mix until real wet.
Add peppers, onions and catsup.
Mix well.
Last, add hamburger and mix thoroughly.

title: penne a la margaret!
directions: Boil water for pasta.
Meanwhile in skillet, heat butter and oil.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add peppers and mushrooms and heat through.
When pasta is almost cooked add the tomatoes and broccoli to mixture in skillet (steam broccoli beforehand, if you prefer them more tender).
Pour mixture over pasta.
Season.
Add cheese if preferred.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Measure 1 cup of water and add only enough to the dry ingredients to make a paste.
Blend into the paste, egg yolks, followed by the remainder of the water and evaporated milk.
Cook over slow fire, stirring mixture frequently.
Add butter during cooking process.
When filling is thick (do not overcook), add vanilla.
Pour into baked pastry shell and top with meringue or whipped cream.
If topped with whipped cream, chill before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as package directs and drain.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Slice cheese in strips and place over broccoli.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over all.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp until they turn pink about 8 minutes. Do Not over cook. Drain and rinse with cold water; drain again. Chop coarsely. Mix rest of ingredients together. Add shrimp and season to taste.

title: stack cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs; set aside.
Mix together flour, spices and soda; set aside.
Mix together molasses and boiling water.
Mix all three mixes together.
Makes a thin batter. Bake in 4 or 5 (9-inch) pans and bake at 375° until brown.
Put layers together with dried apples, apple butter or applesauce.

title: the stain recipe
directions: Add 1 cup each powdered Cascade and Clorox II to 5 gallons of hot water. Soak several articles overnight and launder as usual.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix fruit cocktail or peaches with raisins, chocolate chips, nuts, etc.; put into greased cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix dry over fruit in pan.
Dice oleo up over dry cake mix in pan.
Bake at 325° until light brown, 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter and honey bars
directions: In large saucepan, put honey and boil for 30 seconds.
Turn off heat; add peanut butter.
Stir until blended.
Add cornflakes. Stir well, then pour into a 9 x 13-inch flat greased pan or dish. Press down; sprinkle on chocolate or butterscotch chips.

title: honey mustard dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Makes 1 cup.

title: rotel chip dip
directions: Brown the hamburger meat.
Rinse excess grease from the meat by pouring hot water over it.
Melt the cheese and add the hamburger meat and Ro-Tel.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve warm with chips.

title: pound cake
directions: You need 1 Bundt cake pan.

title: corn bread
directions: Bake in flour skillet at 425° or until golden brown.
Use about 1/4 cup oil in skillet.

title: garlic toast
directions: Cut bread into 3/4 x 1 1/2-inch thick long pieces.
Heat butter, paprika and garlic salt.
Dip bread in milk mixture.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In a large bowl combine the first eight ingredients; mix well. Shape into 2 dozen 1 1/2 inch balls.
Place in greased 2 quart casserole dish.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine softened cheese and milk, mixing until well blended. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Serve with fresh vegetable dippers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: microwave rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave-safe bowl and cover. Microwave on High for 19 minutes for perfect rice every time.

title: taco pie
directions: Pie should be layered in pie plate.
Bottom layer, rolls, then 3/4 c. Doritos, beef, sour cream, cheese and remaining Doritos.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring 1/3 cup oil and 1/2 cup vinegar to a boil. Pour over other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: 14 carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well. Stir in carrots, pineapple and nuts; turn into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans (or large flat glass pan).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bacon-cream cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: garden chicken macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water about 8 minutes until tender; drain well.
Rinse with cold water.
In a bowl combine cooked macaroni, tomatoes, cucumber and green onions.
Stir mayo or salad dressing, dill weed, salt and pepper into macaroni mixture; mix well.
Fold in chicken.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Cover and chill in refrigerator for 3 to 24 hours.

title: kelly's meat and gravy
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess fat. Add onion, pepper, seasonings, and then cover. Let steam on low heat for about 15 minutes. Add soups and continue to simmer covered for about 15 to 20 minutes. Serve over hot biscuits, toast, rice, or potatoes. I prefer to make mine in cast iron.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix crust ingredients well.
Press into small pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Bring first 9 ingredients to a slow simmer.
Add the black-eyed peas, tomatoes and garlic and cook for 30 minutes on medium heat.
Mix bacon drippings and flour and add to cooked mixture.
Heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Crush Oreos, saving 1/2 cup for top.
Melt butter and mix with crushed Oreos.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate mixture for at least 1 hour.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth, then fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip, saving remainder for top.
Spread over crushed Oreos.
Mix pudding (using pie mix with less milk).
Pour over cream cheese and Cool Whip layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Just before serving, sprinkle with 1/2 cup crushed Oreos.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: To make crust:
Lay out and press together the crescent rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake and cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing together.

Spread on cool crust, sprinkle chopped vegetables on top, any combination you prefer (broccoli, tomatoes, mushrooms, celery, carrots, ripe olives, green onions, cauliflower, green peppers, radishes or any other vegetables). Cover with plastic wrap or foil.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: turketti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Put turkey, pimento, green pepper and onion in casserole. Pour in mushroom soup, broth, salt, pepper and 1 1/4 cups of cheese and spaghetti.
Toss with 2 forks until mixed and coated in sauce.
Sprinkle rest of the cheese on top. Preheat oven to 350° and bake 45 minutes until bubbly throughout.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat with onion and bell pepper.
Add regular size cans of tomatoes, kidney beans, hominy or corn, pinto beans with jalapeno and Ro-Tel (juice and all), taco mix and water.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with corn bread or tortilla chips.
Cheddar cheese sprinkled on top adds a delicious touch.

title: pork roast and sauerkraut
directions: Brown pork roast under broiler.
Put pork roast in Dutch oven or roasting pan.
Add sauerkraut with juice, brown sugar and bay leaf.
Cover tightly and put in oven.
Cook at 300° for 3 to 5 hours.

title: potato pinwheels
directions: Boil until done one medium potato, either peeled or unpeeled. While still hot, mash thoroughly.
Begin adding powdered sugar, small amounts at a time until the potato and powdered sugar mixture is at a rolled dough stage.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness. Spread evenly with chunk-style peanut butter and roll up.
Chill 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Slice into 1/4-inch or 1/2-inch pieces. Serve cold.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: easy crock-pot chicken
directions: Place frozen chicken breasts in crock-pot.
Pour bottle of sauce over chicken.
Turn crock-pot on low and cook several hours.

title: parmesan parslied chicken
directions: Mix coating ingredients.
Dip chicken in melted butter and roll in coating mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add butter, if needed, for moistness.

title: low-fat applesauce cookies
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar.
Continue beating until well mixed.
Add flour that has been sifted with soda, salt, spices and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add raisins and applesauce.
Stir until well blended.
Drop on a Teflon cookie sheet and bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Fat content of recipe:
flour 1.5 grams, eggs 120 grams and applesauce 13.5 grams.
Yields 45 cookies.

title: peas almondine
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Cook peas according to package directions.
Omit salt.
Drain.
Stir in sour cream.
Blend in onion soup mix.
Stir in bacon, almonds and pimento.
Heat through.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: Combine meat, beans, oregano and cumin; mix well.
Stuff into uncooked manicotti shells.
Arrange in 10 X 6 X 2 baking dish. Combine water and picante sauce, pour over manicoti shells.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Micro on HI for 10 minutes, (turning dish 1/2 turn once if micro not equipped with turntable).
Turn shells over and micro, covered, on medium for 18 minutes (turning dish 1/2 turn once).
Combine sour cream, green onions and olives.
Spoon down center of dish.
Top with cheese, micro on HI, uncovered, 2-3 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serves 2-3.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Stir hot water and sugar until dissolved. Add pineapple with juice, lemon juice and frozen orange juice. Stir chopped bananas and maraschino cherries. Add to mixture and stir. Put in a container and freeze. Stir several times until frozen.

title: rice pudding
directions: Start cooking rice in water on top of stove, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
When all water is absorbed and rice appears fluffy, begin adding milk.
Pour into large baking dish and place in 350° oven for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir frequently to prevent crust-like topping.
Add salt and sugar.
Longer cooking time makes a better tasting pudding!
Add vanilla towards the end of baking time.
Extra milk can be added and stirred in throughout baking time.

title: potato bud cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and extract.
Add egg and beat.
Stir in Bisquick and potato flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until edges are just beginning to brown.
Place these cookies far apart on the cookie sheet because they spread and flatten out quite a bit. (Yield: about 2 dozen cookies.)

title: maple crunch popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine popcorn and peanuts; set aside. Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in syrup and cinnamon.
Bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda.
Pour over popcorn mixture and toss to coat evenly.

title: magnolia pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Beat in softened cream cheese and sugar. Blend until smooth. Add rind and juice of one lemon and Knox gelatin. Pour into 3 crumb crusts. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. While they are baking, gently combine the remaining sugar and juice and rind of other lemon with the sour cream. Refrigerate until ready to use. Remove pies from oven and allow to cool slightly. Spread sour cream topping on and return to oven for 5 minutes. Refrigerate overnight. Freezes well.

title: creamy turkey mushroom casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart round casserole.
Fry bacon, until crisp and crumble.
Cook and stir onion, celery, green pepper and mushrooms in bacon fat until tender.
Drain, if necessary; stir in soup, sour cream, turkey, salt, pepper and bacon, heating until bubbly.

title: microwave chicken casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine soups, water and raw rice (measured in soup can); bring to boil.
Simmer 7 minutes.
Add chicken cubes. Stir well.
Pour into casserole dish; sprinkle onion rings over top.
Microwave, uncovered, 3 minutes.
Sometimes we decrease water and add cheese in saucepan for a different taste.

title: pear bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, then mix remaining ingredients together, add to dry ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Makes one loaf.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove and cool on rack.

title: easy shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook shrimp and peel.
Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions.
Add other ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: garlic turkey sausage
directions: Combine ingredients and blend.
Makes 16 patties.

title: peach bread
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg and almond extract. In large bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir until blended well. Alternately add flour mixture, peaches and apple juice to butter mixture, stirring until blended well. Stir in almonds, if desired. Grease 9 x 5 loaf pan. Line bottom of pan with waxed or parchment paper (if you do not line the pan, peaches in bread stick). Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until golden brown. Remove form oven and cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: crab meat cakes
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Make into 8 patties and roll in cracker meal.
Fry in deep hot fat until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.	Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: texas governor ann w. richards jalapeno cheese cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 425° for about 25 minutes or until done. This is a wonderful recipe.
It is particularly good with chicken, pork and any vegetable.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening and add sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Sift 3 cups flour with baking powder and soda.
Add to first ingredients, then add remaining 3 cups of flour.
Chill a couple of hours if desired.
Roll out on a floured surface so dough is thick.
Cut out cookies.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Can also drop batter if desired.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, and salt together.
Combine oil, melted chocolate, and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time mixing well.

Add vanilla and dry ingredients and blend thoroughly. Chill several hours or overnight. When ready to bake, roll dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in powdered sugar. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 - 12 minutes at 350°.

title: party dip
directions: With electric mixer, blend soup into cream cheese.
Beat just until smooth.
Mix in remaining ingredients, then chill.
Serve as a dip with crackers or chips.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and allow to cool.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and set aside.
Layer the following ingredients in a punch bowl:
cake, pudding, pie filling, pineapple, fruit cocktail, nuts, coconut and whipped topping.
Repeat layers. Sprinkle top with coconut.

title: potato chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Saute onion in bacon grease for 3 or 4 minutes. Drain off fat.
Add potatoes and water. Cook until potatoes are tender. Add sour cream and soup.
Gradually add milk. Stir in salt, pepper, bacon and parsley.
Heat to serving temperature (not boiling).
If too thick, add milk, chicken broth or water.

title: applesauce barbecue pork chops
directions: Prepare mixture and pour over the 6 pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: southern applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Beat eggs into sugar mixture.
Gradually stir dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Alternately with applesauce.
Blend thoroughly.
Fold in fruits and nuts.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: hickory pot roast
directions: Place roast in roasting pan and cut 1/4-inch slits in roast both ways.
Pour hickory smoke over roast and smother with onions (can be refrigerated overnight). Put roast in oven covered with aluminum foil at 300° for 2 hours.
After 2 hours, take out and place potatoes and carrots around roast; re-cover.
Reduce heat to 200° for 2 more hours.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. (Can be refrigerated overnight before cooking.) Pour into 9 x 13 casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours OR microwave 15 minutes on High. Stir and microwave an additional 15 minutes.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour over margarine.
Spoon fruit over batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.
